nity and laid the groundwork for creating Ethereum.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1535\\\" data-end=\\\"1851\\\">In April 2014, at the North American Bitcoin Conference, Vitalik first presented his vision for Ethereum. Like-minded geeks gathered to make that vision a reality. By July 2014, Ethereum&rsquo;s crowdfunding campaign had raised 31,000 BTC (worth about $18 million at the time), enabling the project to officially launch.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1853\\\" data-end=\\\"1942\\\">On July 30, 2015, the Ethereum mainnet was released with its first version, <em data-start=\\\"1929\\\" data-end=\\\"1939\\\">Frontier<\\/em>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"1949\\\" data-end=\\\"1985\\\">&nbsp;<\\/h2>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"1949\\\" data-end=\\\"1985\\\">II. Shaping Industry Narratives<\\/h2>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"1987\\\" data-end=\\\"2025\\\">1. From ICO Boom to Bubble Burst<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2026\\\" data-end=\\\"2469\\\">In 2017, Ethereum sparked the Initial Coin Offering (ICO) frenzy, rewriting the narrative of the crypto world. As an open smart contract platform, Ethereum made it easy for developers to create and deploy blockchain projects. Countless startups issued tokens on Ethereum. According to ICODATA.IO, only 29 ICO projects launched in 2016, raising just over $90,000. By 2017, the number soared to 876 projects with total funding of $6.2 billion.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2471\\\" data-end=\\\"2672\\\">Many startups raised millions of dollars within minutes&mdash;or even seconds&mdash;through ICOs. By 2017, ICO funding had surpassed traditional venture capital as a key financing method for blockchain startups.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2674\\\" data-end=\\\"2996\\\">But excess bred chaos. While ICOs introduced blockchain to the mainstream, rampant problems also emerged: plagiarized white papers, fake teams, and &ldquo;air coins.&rdquo; This led many countries to ban ICO fundraising. Ethereum itself suffered a major setback: from $1,400 in December 2017, ETH plummeted to just $85 a year later.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2998\\\" data-end=\\\"3161\\\">The bursting of the ICO bubble brought heavy criticism to Ethereum and the crypto industry as a whole. Yet this crash marked the beginning of Ethereum&rsquo;s rebirth.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"3163\\\" data-end=\\\"3203\\\">2. Returning to the Technical Core<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"3204\\\" data-end=\\\"3384\\\">The ICO collapse triggered a crypto winter, during which countless projects went to zero. Ethereum, however, stayed focused, using the downturn to pursue technical breakthroughs.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"3386\\\" data-end=\\\"3635\\\">At the time, Ethereum could only process 15 transactions per second. During congestion, fees soared to hundreds of dollars, earning Ethereum the nickname &ldquo;the world&rsquo;s most expensive computer.&rdquo; Solving this bottleneck became Vitalik&rsquo;s top priority.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"3637\\\" data-end=\\\"3726\\\">In November 2017, Vitalik first proposed the concept of &ldquo;Ethereum 2.0,&rdquo; which included:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul data-start=\\\"3727\\\" data-end=\\\"4056\\\">\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"3727\\\" data-end=\\\"3861\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"3729\\\" data-end=\\\"3861\\\">Transitioning from Proof-of-Work (PoW) to Proof-of-Stake (PoS) to reduce energy consumption and speed up transaction confirmation.<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"3862\\\" data-end=\\\"3949\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"3864\\\" data-end=\\\"3949\\\">Introducing sharding to enable parallel transaction processing and ease congestion.<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"3950\\\" data-end=\\\"4056\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"3952\\\" data-end=\\\"4056\\\">Improving the Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) to boost performance, security, and developer experience.<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"4058\\\" data-end=\\\"4347\\\">This long-term effort bore fruit in December 2020 with the launch of the Ethereum 2.0 mainnet. By December 2021, nearly 8.75 million ETH were staked&mdash;over 14.28% of circulating supply&mdash;backed by more than 273,600 validators, showing strong industry confidence in Ethereum&rsquo;s new trajectory.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"4349\\\" data-end=\\\"4614\\\">Meanwhile, key upgrades like the <em data-start=\\\"4382\\\" data-end=\\\"4398\\\">Constantinople<\\/em> hard fork (February 2019) and the <em data-start=\\\"4433\\\" data-end=\\\"4443\\\">Istanbul<\\/em> hard fork (December 2019) enhanced performance, improved resilience against DoS attacks, enabled interoperability with Zcash, and expanded smart contract functionality.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"4616\\\" data-end=\\\"4815\\\">Following Vitalik&rsquo;s vision, developers also explored &ldquo;Layer 2&rdquo; solutions such as state channels and rollups, allowing faster, cheaper off-chain transactions while relieving pressure on the mainnet.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"4817\\\" data-end=\\\"4908\\\">Between 2018 and 2019, Ethereum&rsquo;s focus on technical refinement reshaped its future path.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"4910\\\" data-end=\\\"4968\\\">3. The DeFi Revolution and Digital Civilization Wave<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"4969\\\" data-end=\\\"5424\\\">In 2020, Compound&rsquo;s liquidity mining ignited the &ldquo;DeFi Summer.&rdquo; Decentralized finance exploded, with countless projects using smart contracts to build lending, trading, insurance, and investment platforms, challenging traditional finance. According to DeFi Pulse, total value locked (TVL) in DeFi grew from $680 million in early 2020 to $240 billion by the end of 2021. Ethereum thus evolved from the &ldquo;Internet of Value&rdquo; into an &ldquo;open financial system.&rdquo;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"5426\\\" data-end=\\\"5795\\\">In 2021, the &ldquo;NFT year&rdquo; began. Collections like <em data-start=\\\"5474\\\" data-end=\\\"5487\\\">CryptoPunks<\\/em> and <em data-start=\\\"5492\\\" data-end=\\\"5514\\\">Bored Ape Yacht Club<\\/em> went viral, while OpenSea became the leading NFT marketplace. The digital art boom revealed Ethereum&rsquo;s potential to power a new era of digital culture. Beeple&rsquo;s <em data-start=\\\"5676\\\" data-end=\\\"5708\\\">Everydays: The First 5000 Days<\\/em> sold at Christie&rsquo;s for $69 million, cementing NFTs&mdash;and Ethereum&mdash;on the global stage.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"5797\\\" data-end=\\\"5849\\\">4. Toward Sustainable Financial Infrastructure<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"5850\\\" data-end=\\\"6112\\\">On September 15, 2022, Ethereum completed <em data-start=\\\"5892\\\" data-end=\\\"5903\\\">The Merge<\\/em>, transitioning fully from PoW to PoS. This reduced energy consumption by 99.95%, resolving long-standing environmental criticisms. Post-Merge, Ethereum became a truly &ldquo;sustainable financial infrastructure.&rdquo;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"6114\\\" data-end=\\\"6391\\\">Before The Merge, Ethereum operated two parallel blockchains: the PoW mainnet (Execution Layer) and the PoS Beacon Chain (Consensus Layer). The Merge unified them under PoS, paving the way for future scalability upgrades like sharding to address congestion and high gas fees.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"6393\\\" data-end=\\\"6635\\\">In April 2023, Ethereum completed the <em data-start=\\\"6431\\\" data-end=\\\"6441\\\">Shapella<\\/em> upgrade, enabling staked ETH withdrawals. This not only restored liquidity to stakers but also deepened Ethereum&rsquo;s integration with the DeFi ecosystem, reinforcing its role in global finance.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"6637\\\" data-end=\\\"6677\\\">5. Moving into Traditional Finance<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"6678\\\" data-end=\\\"7036\\\">On July 23, 2024, U.S. spot Ethereum ETFs launched. Giants like BlackRock, Fidelity, and Grayscale introduced ETH ETFs, giving American investors regulated and convenient access to Ethereum. The ETFs lowered barriers to entry, boosted liquidity and transparency, and drew institutional and retail interest, cementing Ethereum&rsquo;s place in mainstream finance.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"7038\\\" data-end=\\\"7681\\\">Beyond ETFs, traditional companies are increasingly adopting Ethereum as a treasury reserve asset. For instance, SharpLink Gaming held 360,000 ETH (about $1.3 billion) as of July 23, 2024. Ethereum co-founder and Consensys CEO Joe Lubin helped design SharpLink&rsquo;s ETH treasury strategy, urging the company to aggressively accumulate ETH. According to Lubin, SharpLink acquires ETH daily through market-based issuance and stakes it to generate compounded yields. &ldquo;We believe our per-share ETH accumulation rate will outpace any Ethereum&mdash;or even Bitcoin&mdash;related project,&rdquo; Lubin declared, signaling strong market confidence in Ethereum&rsquo;s future.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"7683\\\" data-end=\\\"7796\\\">Ethereum has become not just a blockchain but a bridge between traditional finance and the decentralized world.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"7803\\\" data-end=\\\"7834\\\">&nbsp;<\\/h2>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"7803\\\" data-end=\\\"7834\\\">III. The Battlefield Ahead<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"7836\\\" data-end=\\\"7973\\\">The trend of &ldquo;de-dollarization&rdquo; is increasingly discussed in emerging and developing countries. But will it really happen anytime soon?<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"7975\\\" data-end=\\\"7992\\\">The answer: No.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"7994\\\" data-end=\\\"8388\\\">Over 4 billion people and millions of businesses are actively seeking U.S. dollar access via stablecoins. This represents the greatest expansion of the dollar&rsquo;s network effect in decades. Stablecoins have grown 60-fold since 2020, surpassing $200 billion, bringing millions of new users into the dollar economy. But users want more than digital cash&mdash;they need robust financial infrastructure.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"8390\\\" data-end=\\\"8842\\\">Such infrastructure must be globally accessible, institutionally secure, and resistant to government interference. Ethereum meets all these criteria. As billions flow through stablecoins on Ethereum, participants need a safe, permissionless, and efficient asset to underpin lending, staking, and yield generation. The rise of Ethereum Layer 2 solutions further amplifies ETH demand, creating a feedback loop that benefits Ethereum&rsquo;s price trajectory.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"8844\\\" data-end=\\\"9140\\\">As stablecoin usage on Ethereum grows, so too does demand for ETH. Higher ETH prices and a stronger network attract more institutions and services, accelerating stablecoin adoption. Holding ETH may be the simplest and most effective way to participate in this growing stablecoin-driven economy.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"9147\\\" data-end=\\\"9174\\\">&nbsp;<\\/h2>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"9147\\\" data-end=\\\"9174\\\">IV. Ethereum&rsquo;s Endgame<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"9176\\\" data-end=\\\"9449\\\">From a 19-year-old&rsquo;s vision on paper, through the ICO boom and bust, to technical upgrades, powering DeFi and NFTs, completing The Merge, enabling ETFs, and becoming a corporate treasury asset&mdash;Ethereum has, in just a decade, embodied the epic evolution of cryptocurrency.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"9451\\\" data-end=\\\"9710\\\">We cannot predict what Ethereum will look like in another ten years. But stablecoins already outline a clear near-term trajectory, and their synergy with Ethereum suggests the network will remain the proving ground for the next wave of financial innovation.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"9712\\\" data-end=\\\"9892\\\">Where is Ethereum&rsquo;s endgame? Perhaps it lies hidden in every line of stablecoin transfer code&mdash;or in the stories of everyday people who achieve financial freedom through Ethereum.<\\/p>\",\"id\":null,\"_remove_\":\"0\"}},\"_token\":\"GAvyFfalHkflR59lOApQmnFXj1Dn8fTBPi5y0VBm\",\"_previous_\":\"https:\\/\\/api.gemini-jp.cc\\/admin\\/article\"}', '2025-08-25 19:01:29', '2025-08-25 19:01:29');
INSERT INTO `admin_operation_log` VALUES (3409, 1, 'admin/article', 'POST', '38.92.27.74', '{\"category_id\":null,\"cover\":null,\"_file_\":null,\"status\":\"1\",\"order\":\"1\",\"is_recommend\":\"0\",\"translations\":{\"new_1\":{\"locale\":\"en\",\"title\":\"U.S. SEC Opens Public Comment Period on Canary\\u2019s Staked INJ ETF\",\"excerpt\":null,\"body\":\"<p>The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) is seeking public comment on whether to approve Canary&rsquo;s proposed Staked Injective (INJ) Exchange-Traded Fund (ETF). The SEC has set a 21-day deadline for submitting comments and will decide on the next steps within 90 days.<\\/p>\",\"id\":null,\"_remove_\":\"0\"}},\"_token\":\"GAvyFfalHkflR59lOApQmnFXj1Dn8fTBPi5y0VBm\",\"_previous_\":\"https:\\/\\/api.gemini-jp.cc\\/admin\\/article\"}', '2025-08-25 19:03:16', '2025-08-25 19:03:16');
