INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (86, 43, 'zh-CN', '什么是区块链？', '<p>什么是呢，本质上讲，区块链是一种分布式、去中心化的网络数据库系统，这个系统会让数据的存储、更新、维护、操作变得不同。</p><p>我们今天要讲的区块链呢，它有四项不可缺的核心技术，分别是：分布式存储、共识机制、密码学原理、智能合约。</p><p><br></p><p>那么我们今天就讲一讲，与传统数据处理相比，区块链到底有什么不同，帮助大家了解，让大家对区块链有一个总的认知。</p><p><br></p><p>一、区块链中的数据存储：块链式数据结构</p><p><br></p><p>在数据存储方面，区块链技术利用的是“块链式数据结构”来验证与存储数据的。块链式结构是什么意思呢？铁链子大家都见过吧，一环套一环那种，其实，每一环我们可以看作是一个区块，很多环节扣在一起就形成了区块链。</p><p><br></p><p>区块里存储的是数据，和普通存储数据的不同之处在于：在区块链上，后一个区块里的数据是包含前一个区块里的数据的。</p><p><br></p><p>以读书为例：我们平时看书，看完第一页，接着读第二页、第三页……那在区块链里面呢，如果给每个区块标注上页码，那么第二页的内容是包含第一页的内容的，第三页的内容包含第一页和第二页的内容……第十页包含了前九页的内容，就是这样一个层层嵌套的链条。这样一来，就可以追溯到最本源的数据了，这就是区块链的可追溯性。</p><p><br></p><p>二、区块链中的数据更新：分布式节点共识算法</p><p><br></p><p>在数据更新方面，区块链技术是利用“分布式节点共识算法”来生成和更新数据。</p><p><br></p><p>每每生成新的区块（也就是更新数据的时候），都需要通过一种算法获得全网51%以上节点的认可才能构成新的区块，说白了就是投票，超过半数人同意就可以生成。这就使得区块链上的数据不容篡改。</p><p><br></p><p>我们还是打一个比喻来解释：我们把区块链比作一个账本，因为都是记录数据的嘛。传统世界里，记账权在于记账先生，账本属于记账先生一个人的；在区块链里面，每一个人都拥有这个账本，大家一起来记账，想要更新账目呢，就要投票，半数人以上赞成才可以去更新账目数据。</p><p><br></p><p>在这个过程中，我们会涉及到这么几个名词：分布式、节点、共识算法：</p><p><br></p><p>每个人都记账（也就是人人拥有账本，账本分散在每个人手里）这就是所谓的“分布式”；大家讨论、投票产生的、一致赞同的记账办法，就是所谓的“共识算法”；节点就更简单了，参与记账的每一个人就可以看做是一个节点。</p><p><br></p><p>三、 区块链中的数据维护：密码学</p><p><br></p><p>接下来到了数据维护阶段，区块链的不同之处就在于：它利用密码学的方式来保证数据传输和访问的安全。</p><p><br></p><p>那么，区块链中所应用的密码学原理主要有以下这么几个：哈希算法、Merkle哈希树、椭圆曲线算法、Base58。这些原理，其实呢，他们都是通过一系列复杂的运算以及换算，来保证区块链上数据安全。</p><p><br></p><p>四、 区块链中的数据操作：智能合约</p><p><br></p><p>最后就进入到了数据的操作阶段，也就是我们接着要说的“智能合约”。</p><p><br></p><p>智能合约，是由计算机程序定义并自动执行的承诺协议，说白了，就是用代码执行的一套交易准则，类似于现在的信用卡自动还款功能，开启这个功能，您自己什么都不用管，到期银行会自动扣除您欠的钱。</p><p><br></p><p>智能合约的突出优势就是，很大程度上避免了由信任产生的一系列问题。我们很多人，都遇到过被借钱的事情：朋友手头紧了跟你借2000块钱，承诺下个月发了工资还钱，到了下个月他又找别的借口不还，拖来托去这事儿就没谱了。本来没多少钱，还是朋友，虽然你很郁闷，这事也就算了。</p><p><br></p><p>那么，有了智能合约以后，他就不能赖账了，因为在智能合约上，一旦触发合约中的条款，代码就会自动执行，不管他愿不愿意，只要他发了工资、账户上有了钱，他就得还你。</p><p><br></p><p>最后总结一下今天的内容，今天呢我们主要通过数据存储操作的这么一个流程，介绍了区块链的基本情况。我们对此做一个总结，可以发现区块链中有四项不可缺的核心技术，分别是：分布式存储、共识机制、密码学原理、智能合约。</p><p><br></p><p>那么，我们可以这样理解：分布式存储对应的是数据存储这个阶段，共识机制对应的是数据的处理更新这个阶段，密码学对应的是数据安全，智能合约对应的是数据的操作问题。</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (87, 44, 'zh-CN', '如何充提币-以比特币为例', '<p>平台间的充币、提币可以通过资产管理-充币/提币完成：</p><p>充币：</p><p>点击资产管理中的充币</p><p>选择您想要充值的币种，以BTC为例</p><p>出现BTC对应的充值地址及注意事项，需要您将此地址复制到汇出方平台进行操作。</p><p>提币</p><p>点击资产管理中的提币</p><p>提币分为普通提币和内部转账，普提提币是通过区块确认从而到其他平台的提币（需要网络旷工手续费），内部转账是平台内部进行转账（包括合作交易平台），实时到账不收取手续费。</p><p>以BTC为例，需要将其他平台的充币地址进行复制粘贴，按照步骤进行填写提币即可。</p><p>内部转账是通过账户绑定的手机号码或者邮箱进行转账,账户名称那一栏直接填写收币方账户的手机号码或者邮箱即可</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (88, 45, 'zh-CN', '什么是KYC验证？如何完成KYC验证？', '<p>什么是KYC</p><p>KYC（Know your customer）政策（即充分了解你的客户）对账户持有人的强化审查，是反洗钱用于预防腐败的制度基础。</p><p>为什么做KYC</p><p>KYC政策不仅要求金融机构实行账户实名制，了解账户的实际控制人和交易的实际收益人，还要求对客户的身份、常住地址或企业所从事的业务进行充分的了解，并采取相应的措施。</p><p>如何进行KYC认证？</p><p>登录账户，点击小人头像选择身份认证。</p><p>根据步骤完成1级、2级、3级认证。</p><p>1级认证需要填写有效证件信息</p><p>2级认证需要上传有效证件正反面照片，完成后需要进行人脸识别，需要使用手机扫描页面二维码操作（需要手机端有支付宝）</p><p>3级认证需要通过手机APP进行认证，进行认证时需要口述文案。</p><p>手机APP与网页端一致。</p><p>认证须知：</p><p>1、请根据提示的内容，完成认证视频的录制。录制过程中会要求拍摄您的身份证或护照，请务必提前准备好您的证件。（国内用户只能使用身份证进行认证，不可以使用护照）</p><p>2、拍摄的每一步骤都会有文字提示，请按照文字提示进行操作。</p><p>3、每段视频拍摄好后，建议您都打开检查一下，如果拍摄效果不清晰的话需要您重新进行录制。否则很可能因为视频效果不清晰而审核不过。</p><p>4、视频上传对于流量和网速要求较高，视频上传预计占用您20M的流量，强烈建议您在WIFI环境下进行视频认证。 </p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (89, 46, 'zh-CN', '零基础学习币市分析| 4 看跌K线组合', '<p>涨跌有趋势，读懂价格语言；</p><p>买卖有信号，告别感觉交易。</p><p>本节我们继续学习K线的组合应用——看跌组合。</p><p>夕阳无限好，已是近黄昏。黄昏之星的出现，预示币价上涨行情告一段落，调整即将来临。</p><p>什么样的K线组合是黄昏之星呢？</p><p>标准的黄昏之星由三根K线组合而成，首先是一根较大的阳线，随后紧跟一根类似“十字”的星线，第三根K线是一根较大的阴线。黄昏之星是否成立，对第三根阴线的长度有着明确的要求，它的收盘价格一定要低于第一根阳线实体的50%。</p><p>在确定黄昏之星有效以后，我们可以通过最后一根阴线收盘价的位置，来判断后市看跌力度强弱。如图，阴线收盘价格刚刚超过50%及格线，那么这种情况下的看跌力度比较弱。若后阴线收盘价格与前阳线开盘价格持平，则认为看跌力度较强。若后阴线收盘价格明显低于前阳线开盘价格，则认为看跌力度相当强劲。</p><p>刚刚所讲是最标准的黄昏之星组合，但在实际走势中，黄昏之星会有一些变化。那么市场中真实的黄昏之星是怎样的呢？</p><p>例如三种黄昏之星的样子，中间由两根小K线组成。我们将它还原到实际走势图中。币价在大涨之后的高位区出现黄昏之星，后市币价出现大幅调整。+</p><p>中间K线并不是标准的十字星线，而是带有长上影线的小K线。截图来自OKEx ，BTC/USD 2小时图表，在高位出现黄昏之星后，币价滞涨回落</p><p>中间出现两根十字星，阴线力度明显大于阳线。币价在大涨后出现看跌力度强劲的黄昏之星，在高位震荡后最终出现大跌。有些时候黄昏之星会连续出现两个，甚至更多。BTC/USDT这段下跌走势途中，相隔不远的两个反弹高位都出现了黄昏之星，币价随后继续下跌。</p><p>接下来我们学习第二种看跌K线组合–看跌吞没。</p><p>首先，看一下看跌吞没的特征。后一根阴线实体，完全覆盖前一根阳线实体，如同阳线被阴线吞噬掉一般。说明空头力量正在大举反攻。因此得名看跌吞没。</p><p>那么如何判断看跌力度呢？</p><p>下跌阴线实体刚刚将阳线实体吞没，该种情况看跌力度较弱；阴线实体收盘价明显低于阳线开盘价，阴线长度甚至达到阳线的两倍，该种情况看跌力度很强；阴线实体一举将多根阳线吞没，该种情况看跌力度非常强劲。</p><p>在市场中存在很多非标准的看跌吞没组合，那实际的看跌吞没组合是怎样的呢？</p><p>三种看跌吞没组合的变体。</p><p>币价大幅上涨后出现了一阴吞多阳的强劲看跌吞没组合后，币价出现连续下跌。</p><p>在下跌行情的反弹高点，出现看跌吞没组合，币价结束反弹继续下行。</p><p>币价在连续大涨后，出现看跌吞没组合，随后展开大幅下跌。</p><p>第三种看跌K线组合：塔形顶</p><p>塔形顶，左边是一根中阳线或大阳线；中间由若干根小k线组成，通常在5根以上；右边是一根中阴线或大阴线。整体看上去就像一座宝塔，因此得名塔形顶。</p><p>一个有效的塔形顶要满足：最后一根阴线的收盘价要低于前面大阴线实体的50%以下；塔形顶所展现的是：市场中做多力量逐步衰竭，多空达成平衡，最后到下跌力度增强的过程。</p><p>在确定塔形顶有效后，我们可以通过最后一根阴线收盘价的位置，来判断后市看跌力度的强弱。如图，若阴线收盘价刚刚超过50%及格线，那么这种情况下看跌力度相对比较弱；若后阴线收盘价基本与前阳线开盘价持平，则认为看跌力度较强；若后阴线收盘价明显低于前阳线开盘价，则看跌力度相当强劲。</p><p>当然，在实际走势中塔形顶并不像我们示意图中展示的这么完美。要活学活用。我们看一下市场实际中的塔形顶是怎样的。</p><p>变化一，中间多根小K线带有长影线。在大幅度上涨后出现塔形顶组合，之后币价连续下跌，并跌穿前期低点。</p><p>变化二，塔形顶中间部分并不都是非常小的K线构成，K线震荡幅度较大。币价在一段反弹行情中出现塔形顶，随后继续大幅下跌。</p><p>最后我们回顾一下本期内容：</p><p>三种典型的看跌组合。第一种，黄昏之星，预示黑暗即将降临；第二种，看跌吞没，空头力挽狂澜；第三种，塔形顶，多头逐步缴械投降。</p><p>本节课程就到这里，下节课我们将分享K线组合位置重要性。</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (90, 47, 'zh-CN', '零基础学币市分析|1 从价格到K线', '<p>涨跌有趋势，读懂价格语言；</p><p>买卖有信号，告别感觉交易。</p><p>今天我们一起学习，技术分析中最基础的元素——K线。K线是当今最为普遍的价格标记法。</p><p>先来看一下，一天中价格在市场中是如何运行的。</p><p>在没有经过K线标记法处理时，某投资品的价格是这样的，无数的价格连在一起形成一条看起来毫无规律的曲线图。看起来有些乱是不是？</p><p>下面，我们做一下简单的技术分析处理，标记一下其中重要的数据，</p><p>开盘价、收盘价、最高价、最低价。</p><p>我们过滤掉其中繁乱的价格变化，将其绘制成折线图。</p><p>这样看起来是不是清晰很多？</p><p>可不可以，用更简单的表示它呢？</p><p>当然可以，K线图了解一下。</p><p>这样处理，将开盘价、收盘价、最低价、最高价，平移到一条垂直线上。开盘价与收盘价之间构成K线实体，我们用较粗线条表示，实体到最高价和最低价之间我们用细线条表示，分别构成上影线和下影线。</p><p>收盘价低于开盘价的，我们用红色标记实体（答案在这里哦），表示该时段价格下跌，通常称为阴线。收盘价高于开盘价的，我们用绿色标记实体，表示该时段价格上涨，通常称之为阳线。（当然部分市场会使用相反颜色标记K线涨跌。）</p><p>当我们把每一天的K线连在一起，就会出现我们常见的K线图样子。</p><p>每一根红色或绿色的K线都代表一天的价格变化数据。</p><p>一天的价格走势可以用一根K线表示，那么一分钟、一个小时、一星期呢？</p><p>根据统计价格变化的时间范围的不同，我们将K线分为不同的周期。这是多条一分钟K线连在一起的样子，这是多条“周K线”连在一起的样子。</p><p>周期的划分非常灵活多样，几分钟、几小时、几天、几周或是几个月都可以。</p><p>K线，在投资市场分析中有什么作用？</p><p>特定的K线形态或特定的K线组合出现后，大概率会发生特定的价格走势。</p><p>因为价格包含一切市场行为，历史会惊人的相似。</p><p>后续我们再来分享，通过观察K线规律性排列，预判未来价格涨跌的方法。</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (91, 48, 'zh-CN', '零基础学币市分析|3 看涨K线组合', '<p>涨跌有趋势，读懂价格语言；</p><p>买卖有信号，告别感觉交易。</p><p>本章我们一起学习K线组合的应用，今天分享K线的看涨组合。</p><p>黑夜即将逝去，美好的一天就要开始，启明之星的出现，预示币价将迎来一轮上涨行情。</p><p>什么样的K线组合是启明之星呢？</p><p>标准的启明之星由三根K线组合而成，首先是一根较大的阴线，随后紧跟一根类似“十字”的星线，第三根K线是一根较大阳线。启明之星是否成立，对第三根阳线的长度有着明确的要求，它的收盘价格一定要高于第一根阴线实体的50%价位。</p><p>在确定启明之星有效后，我们还可以通过第三根阳线收盘价的位置，来判断后市看涨力度强弱。如图，若阳线收盘价格刚刚超过50%及格线，那么这种情况下的看涨力度是比较弱势的。若后阳线收盘价格与前阴线开盘价格持平，则认为看涨力度较强。若后阳线收盘价明显高于前阴线开盘价，则看涨力度更强劲。</p><p>刚刚所讲，是最标准的启明之星组合，但在实际的走势中，启明之星会有一些变化。那么市场中真实的启明之星是怎么样的呢？</p><p>三种启明之星的样子，中间并不是“十字”星，而更像是“T字”线。我们将它还原到真实的走势图中。</p><p>币价大跌，出现启明之星，后市币价止跌反弹。</p><p>中间由两根小K线组成。币价在上涨途中出现启明之星，后市币价继续上涨。</p><p>由三根小K线或星线组成。币价大幅下跌，出现启明之星，随后币价止跌反转。</p><p>接下来我们学习第二种看涨K线组合——看涨吞没。</p><p>首先，看一下看涨吞没的特征。后一根阳线实体，完全覆盖前面阴线实体，如同阴线被阳线吞噬掉一般，表明多头力量正在大举反攻。因此得名看涨吞没。</p><p>如何判断看涨力度呢？</p><p>上涨阳线实体刚刚吞前面下跌阴线实体，该组合看涨力度最弱；阳线实体明显高于前面阴线实体，甚至达到前阴线的两倍，该组合看涨力度很强；阳线实体一举吞没前面多根阴线，该组合看涨力度最强。</p><p>在市场中存在着很多非标准的看涨吞没组合，那实际的“看涨吞没”是怎样的呢？</p><p>三种看涨吞没组合的样子，阳线并不需要完全吞没前面阴线的影线部分。</p><p>币价大跌后出现看涨吞没组合，后市止跌并出现大幅反弹；</p><p>大阳线吞没两根小阴线，形成看涨吞没，随后展开一波上涨走势；</p><p>阳线一举吞没三根阴线，后市出现大幅上涨。</p><p>第三种看涨K线组合–塔形底。</p><p>塔形底，左边是一根中阴线或大阴线；中间由若干根小K线组成，通常再5根以上；右边是一根中阳线或大阳线。整体看上去就像一个倒过来的宝塔，因此得名塔形底。</p><p>一个有效塔形底要满足：最后一根阳线的收盘价格要超过前面大阴线实体的50%。</p><p>塔形底展现的是：市场中做空力量逐渐减弱，至多空力量平衡，最后到上涨力度增强的过程。</p><p>在确定塔型底有效后，我们还可以通过最后一根阳线收盘价的位置，来判断后市看涨力度强弱。如图，若阳线收盘价格刚刚超过50%及格线，那么这种情况下的看涨力度是比较弱势的。若后阳线收盘价格与前阴线开盘价格持平，则认为看涨力度较强。若后阳线收盘价明显高于前阴线开盘价，则看涨力度更强劲。</p><p>当然，在实际走势中塔形底并不像我们示意图中展示的这么完美。所以要灵活变通。我们看一下市场中实际的“塔形底”是怎样的。</p><p>变化一，实际样子非常接近塔形底的示意图。塔形底出现在上涨趋势中，再次奠定了上涨优势，随后展开一轮伶俐的上涨行情。</p><p>变化二，塔型底中间部分并不都是非常小的K线构成，K线震荡幅度较大。币价大跌后形成塔型底，价格止跌，形成反转。</p><p>最后我们回顾一下我们这一期的内容，</p><p>三种典型的看涨K线组合。第一种，启明之星，预示着光明；第二种，看涨吞没，空方力量被多方快速绞杀；第三种，塔形底，看多力量的步步为营。</p><p>本节课程就到这里，下节课我们将分享认识看跌K线组合。</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (92, 49, 'zh-CN', '零基础学习币市分析| 2 单根K线的演变及寓意', '<p>涨跌有趋势，读懂价格语言；</p><p>买卖有信号，告别感觉交易。</p><p>上一章节，我们初步认识了K线及其结构，可认识K线有什么用呢？续课程，我将逐步为大家揭晓答案。</p><p>今天我们一起学习单根K线的演变和寓意。</p><p>首先来看一下，K线在连续的价格变化中是如何演变的。</p><p>“一字线”，开盘价与收盘价为同一价格。常常出现在开盘瞬间、成交非常匮乏时 或 股市开盘封涨跌停时。</p><p>伴随市场的逐渐活跃，价格出现变动。形成图示实体较短的“小K线”。左边表示价格上涨，通常称为“小阳线”，右边表示价格下跌，通常称为“小阴线”。</p><p>越发活跃的市场，形成图示实体较长的“中阳线”和“中阴线”。</p><p>该时段交易极度活跃，形成左边“大阳线”和右边“大阴线”。</p><p>那么影线是如何形成的呢？</p><p>我们回到刚刚开盘的样子。</p><p>价格逐渐下跌。</p><p>当价格跌至某一价格时，市场逐渐出现主动买入的投资者，将价格一步一步推升上去，形成下影线。K线实体较小，只有下影线的K线，通常称为“锤子线”。</p><p>当K线实体成为一条细线时，我们称为“T字线”。</p><p>随着买入力量越来越强，币价逐渐上涨，形成两种看涨阳线。</p><p>当价格上涨至一定高度，市场逐渐出现主动卖出的投资者，将币价慢慢打压下去，形成上影线，K线实体较小，只有上影线的K线，通常称为“倒锤线”。</p><p>卖盘逐渐增加，打压价格继续下跌，最终收盘价格与开盘价格相同。十字架的K线称为“十字星线”，其形似墓碑，通常称为“墓碑线”，也可以叫“倒T字线”。</p><p>我们通过K线的一步步变化，认识了很多K线，那K线一共有多少种样子呢？</p><p>这些K线又应该如何分类呢？</p><p>我们将各式各样的K线有序排列在一起。横竖相乘，一共42种。我们先说明K线实体长短的寓意。</p><p>第一行，实体短的绿色小阳线，寓意上涨力量软弱。</p><p>第二行，实体较长的绿色中阳线，寓意上涨力量强。</p><p>第三行，实体很长的绿色大阳线，寓意上涨力量占据绝对优势。</p><p>第四行，实体呈细线状，统称星线，寓意多空争夺激烈，势均力敌。</p><p>第五行，实体短的红色小阴线，寓意下跌力量软弱。</p><p>第六行，实体较长的红色中阴线，寓意下跌力量强。</p><p>第七行，实体很长的红色大阴线，寓意下跌力量占据绝对优势。接下来我们揭开上下影线长短的寓意。</p><p>第一列，K线无上下影线，我们通常称为光头光脚，寓意局势一边倒。阳线表示多头强势，阴线表示空头强势。</p><p>第二列，只有下影线，看起来像K线没长头发，因此常叫秃顶。寓意下有支撑，下影线越长，支撑越强。</p><p>第三列，K线只有上影线，通常称为赤脚。寓意上有阻力，上影线越长，阻力越强。</p><p>第四列，上下影线长度几乎相等，寓意支撑与阻力均有，且旗鼓相当。</p><p>第五列，下影线较上影线长些，寓意下方支撑大于上方阻力。</p><p>第六列，上影线较下影线长，寓意上方阻力大于下方支撑。将无数组这样的K线排列在一起，就构成了我们常看到的价格走势图。</p><p>本节课程就到这里，下节课我们将分享，通过观察K线规律性排列，预判未来价格涨跌的方法。</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (93, 50, 'zh-CN', '比特币BTC减半套利策略：交易“减半”', '<p>第三次BTC减半预计将在2020年5月12日发生。有相当多的用户认为BTC价格会因为产量减半，供不应求而上涨。本文，我们利用历史数据回测，探究如何从事件套利的角度交易“减半”。</p><p>历史数据</p><p>2020 年 4 月，BCH 和 BSV 分别于8日和10日发生了减半，两者对BTC 的价格如图所示。对BTC价格可以有效地消除市场波动影响。</p><p>我们可以看到，价格高峰发生在减半当天。作为一名量化交易者，我相信短期价格是受供求关系驱动的。从基本面角度分析，通货膨胀率降低导致价格上涨，这种影响在短期内是可以忽略的。不难想象，减半新闻铺天盖地，人们情绪高涨时，价格会上升至最高点。从百度指数和谷歌指数均可看出，BCH和BSV的搜索率在减半时达到顶峰，这意味着减半时需求也达到最高。我推测我们可以使用所谓的就谣言而入，就新闻而沽(Buy on Rumours, Sell on News)策略。</p><p>比特币BTC减半套利策略：交易“减半”</p><p>简单多空策略回测</p><p>百度搜索率通常从减半发生的3天前开始上涨，并在减半日达到峰值，之后开始下降。利用 LTC（2019 年 8 月 5 日发生减半）、BCH 和 BSV的历史数据，我们提出了一个简单的交易策略，即减半前买入做多，在减半日做空达到反向头寸，并在 3 天后平仓。我们将交易以BTC报价的币对以消除市场波动噪音。如例一所示，这三个简单的交易：提前3天买入~1BTC的减半币种，在减半日当日双倍做空，得到~1BTC空仓，减半3天后平仓，给我们带来了共约33.84%， 平均约11.28%的收益。</p><p>总收益约为 0.3384BTC，即33.84%，均值约为11.28%</p><p>如何应用于即将到来的 BTC 减半</p><p>上述回测显示，在低市值币种市场，“就谣言而入，就新闻而沽(Buy on Rumours, Sell on News)”是一种可用的alpha。但是，将这种策略移植到 BTC 会稍有不同，因为对冲市场波动不是件易事。在上面的例子中，本质上delta为0，因为我们总是在以BTC进行买卖。为了进行类似的BTC减半交易，我们可以选择以USD交易或以USDT进行交易，亦可选择用ETH对冲。用户可以自行选择最佳方式。当然，如果没有现货持仓，用户可以在OKEx杠杆交易平台借币完成上述操作，或者可以选择交易USDT永续合约。</p><p>结论</p><p>本文我们研究了一种事件驱动套利交易，我们在一个币种减半前做多，减半时做空。我们推测，由于减半新闻盛行，市场需求随着减半的到来逐渐增加，但减半后，买入压力逐渐消失，导致价格开始下跌。我们利用以BTC报价的币对进行了delta中性的回测，最后讨论了如何将这个逻辑应用于即将到来的2020年5月BTC的减半。</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (94, 51, 'zh-CN', '区块链如何改变商业价值？唯有颠覆！', '<p>2018年，市场泡沫破裂后，区块链技术本身却获得了政府，公共服务组织和一些私营企业的青睐。目前或许是我们关注区块链技术的最佳时机。区块链技术能否为企业和消费者带来价值变化？区块链可以产生多大商业价值？区块链是否可以创造出比现有业务更具竞争性的商业模式？这里，让我们从价值，价格和成本三个方面来详细讨论区块链技术可能带来的商业价值。</p><p>成本：谁在买单？</p><p>首先，我们不要忘记一些基本原则：价格和成本决定了公司的利润，而价格和价值则产生消费者剩余（consumer’s surplus）。</p><p>价值，价格和成本框架</p><p>从服务商的角度来看，降低成本或（和）提高价格会增加其利润。许多人认为区块链技术降低了经营企业的成本，但这种说法存在争议。与运行中心化数据服务器或网络的成本相比，区块链技术确实可以节省这些成本。然而，要做到让参与区块链网络的节点提供稳定的服务质量，可能会产生意想不到的成本。众所周知，跟中心化网络相比，区块链没有效率优势。</p><p>我们从很多项目中都可以看出，随着业务的增长，“低效成本（inefficiency cost）” 甚至会高于使用区块链技术所节省的成本。正如以太坊创始人Vitalik Buterin所言：“亚马逊EC2云服务的中等规模计算成本为每小时0.04美元，而在以太坊执行相同任务的成本约为每200毫秒13.40美元，比亚马逊高出140万倍。”这表明在效率层面还有很大的提升空间。</p><p>随着业务的发展，区块链的扩展局限和低效率成本问题会变得更加严重。因此，我们不能简单地认为经营区块链业务的总成本将比以前大幅减少。</p><p>然而，有趣的是，区块链业务中往往是消费者为成本买单。</p><p>与区块链商业模式不同，在传统的商业模式中，公司搭建和维护能够处理大量用户请求的中心化网络服务器。公司先承担运行此类网络的成本，后从服务用户中获取利润。然而，在区块链商业模式中，公司不负责处理用户请求，而由“自愿参与的节点”承担，用户支付节点奖励费用。例如，当用户使用以太坊网络上的DAPP时，需要支付节点一定的费用来处理请求。费用可以是DAPP上的通证，也可以是ETH。</p><p>价格：从看不见到看得见</p><p>价格包括成本和公司的利润。让我们来想一想每天使用IT服务支付了多少钱。令人惊讶的是，“付费使用服务”的做法在现有的IT业务中已经很少见了。一旦连接到互联网，用户每次向Google发送电子邮件时都不需要再支付一分钱，除非要充值高级会员来跳过广告或扩展云存储，大多数IT公司都不会向用户索取费用。</p><p>但这并不意味着这些服务是完全免费的。作为回报，用户需要将其数据控制权交给服务商和广告商，而这是公司业务的主要收入来源。我们所在的世界充满着欢迎各类 “免费注册并使用我们的服务”，而这实际上都是一种“无形的价格标签”。</p><p>但是，在基于区块链的服务中，价格标签变得更加明显。在区块链网络中，服务商不再管理、掌握用户数据，用户自己掌握其数据的所有权。一些区块链企业允许其用户“出售”数据来赚取通证，或者支付使用服务的费用。这就是区块链的商业价值。问题是，用户习惯了看似免费的服务，当基于区块链的服务明码标价的时候，用户是否会认为标价合理呢？</p><p>价值：理念超过实用性？</p><p>“价值”是区块链业务中最棘手的部分。企业的价值通常被定义为利润，而对消费者而言，这一单词的含义更加复杂。简单来说，价值就是“消费者愿意购买产品或服务的原因”。如区块链公司的广告词强调“隐私”和“透明”，而传统广告强调速度，价格优势或便利性。这又会产生一系列新的问题：消费者是否愿意牺牲效率和响应及时的客户服务而去使用区块链服务？区块链业务所传递的价值，如隐私和抗审查，是否足以吸引大量消费者群体？</p><p>区块链如何改变商业价值？唯有颠覆</p><p>俗话说，没有恶就没有善。在区块链行业中，有些概念一开始就非常明确，如去中心化是好的，而中心化是不好的。很多区块链项目被指责“不够去中心化”、“伪区块链”。我们已经见证了太多区块链商业模式失败，它们盲目强调好的愿景而忽视了消费者的其他需求。理念本身并不能推动行业的长远发展。有人认为区块链商业模式中通证经济和去中心化的理念具有魔力，可以吸引消费者来这个生态追求经济回报。但是，这种说法并没有现实案例来支撑。</p><p>我们必须承认，大多数通证经济都是服务投资者而非消费者的。人可以轻易的失去对理念的信仰，但却不会轻易放弃好的实际体验。只有当区块链商业公司重视用户体验时，理念才能被消费者所接受。</p><p>超越竞争对手</p><p>如果未来区块链业务可以击败强大的竞争对手，理想情况将会如下图所示：成本和价格降低，消费者剩余增加，最终产生的总价值超过其竞争对手。没有人能够确定这种理想情况是否会变为现实。或许区块链业务的盈利率会低于竞争对手。注：下图中成本，价格和价值的占有比例可能会因公司而异。</p><p>理想中的区块链业务框架与其竞争对手的业务框架</p><p>目前看来，区块链公司在价值，价格和成本三个方面都不存在优势。低效成本太高，消费者习惯于使用“免费”服务，区块链商业模式的理念能否吸引大众消费者仍是个疑问。当然不确定性中存在着积极意义。</p><p>根据“创新者的窘境（Innovator’ Dilemma）”理论，新技术会颠覆现有的市场，甚至导致一些巨头破产。这一理论认为 “颠覆性技术”往往改变了市场的基本价值主张，导致了急剧的范式转移，使得巨头企业无法适应。</p><p>“创新者的窘境”理论认为颠覆性技术最初的性能表现较差，容量低于现有的解决方案。虽然目前的价值，价格和成本框架无法说明区块链产业具有光明的前景，但或许区块链会创造一种全新的范例。区块链技术已经改变了部分人的思考方式，让他们意识到中心化机构和中介所带来的问题。即使区块链技术无法解决这些问题并最终消失，遗留下来的东西也会持续下去，促进下一个颠覆性技术的出现。</p><p>区块链技术的商业模式或许无法创造出人类历史上最赚钱的业务，但它有可能打破目前中心化公司将追求利益最大化作为准则的商业运作理念—-而创造一种新的常态。让我们在行业最艰难的时候依然心存希望。</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (95, 52, 'zh-CN', '莱特币（LTC）现状调查研究（上）', '<p>（LTC）简介</p><p>1）莱特币（LTC）的前世今生</p><p>莱特币（Litecoin），简写LTC，货币符号Ł，创始者李启威（Charlie Lee），LTC代表着轻量级，是对比来讲更为轻量级的数字货币。它与比特币（BTC）在技术上具有相同的实现原理，其创造和转让基于一种开源的加密协议，不受到任何中央机构的管理。</p><p>历史大事记：</p><p>2011年10月7日莱特币通过Github上面的开源客户端进行发布。</p><p>2015年8月26日，莱特币首次减半，每个区块产出量由50降至25个莱特币。</p><p>2016年7月3日，莱特币内核开发团队和莱特币协会发布了“莱特币官方2016年开发路线图”，宣称将发布带有“隔离见证”、“闪电网络”、“智能合约”等功能的新版本。</p><p>2017年5月11日，隔离见证在莱特币第1201536个区块正式激活，莱特币用户可使用隔离见证这种新的交易方式。</p><p>2017年6月21日，莱特币创始人正式宣布莱特币闪电网络上线。闪电网络本质上是使用了哈希时间锁定智能合约来安全地进行0确认交易的一种机制。</p><p>莱特币拥有完整的产业链和充分的流动性，全球莱特币ATM的数量仅次于比特币，矿工和算力、交易平台、开发者、接受支付的商家和粉丝持续增长。</p><p>2）莱特币的机制</p><p>莱特币被称为是“数字白银”，是第一个基于Scrypt算法的网络数字货币，与比特币相比，莱特币具有三个显著差异：</p><p>（1）莱特币网络每2.5分钟（而不是10分钟）就可以处理一个块，提供更快的交易确认。</p><p>（2）莱特币网络预期产出8400万个莱特币，是比特币发行货币量的四倍。</p><p>（3）莱特币在工作量证明算法中使用了由Colin Percival首次提出的Scrypt加密算法，相比于比特币使用的SHA256算法，Scrypt算法对挖掘处理能力要求不高，只需要高速访问内存，更容易在普通计算机上挖矿。Scrpyt算法由于其内存依赖的设计特别符合对抗专业矿机的设计，成为数字货币算法发展的一个主要应用方向。Scrpyt算法提醒了人们对于算力中心化的认识，开启了人们对于hash计算去中心化安全的探索，促进了区块链系统向更好的方向发展。</p><p>3）莱特币减产</p><p>每4年，莱特币将进行减产，每个区块挖出的莱特币减半，上一次减半发生在2015年8月26日，莱特币的区块奖励由50个减半到25个。产量减半从理论上来说会导致供需不平衡，价格上涨，但实际情况却有很多影响因素，15年莱特币减半从其价格表现上可以看出，减半后并没有发生价格上涨，反而有些跌幅。从今天的视角看过去，有几个原因可以作为解释。</p><p>2015年LTC减半前后两个月的走势</p><p>一是在这之前，LTC已经进行了充分的上涨，7月10日曾达到当时最高点8.967美金，市场预期已经得到了充分的体现。二是当时整个数字货币的体量还十分小，应用场景也很有限，过度的炒作使其价格过多偏离价值，实际需求占比很小，减半影响甚微。第三，当价格没有上涨的情况下，减半致使矿工立减一半，高成本的矿工将入不敷出，只得选择关机。而实际上，LTC算力在减半后有一定幅度的下降，价格受此影响反而持续走低。因此8月27日，莱特币已经迎来了减半之后的第一次难度调整，降低7.61%。</p><p>这是发生在2015年的历史，历史不代表未来，现在整个加密货币市场已经不能同日而语，LTC也是如此，接下来OKEx Research将就LTC目前的状况做全面的研究和分析。</p><p>2. 莱特币（LTC）的现状</p><p>LTC目前基本情况</p><p>LTC总供给量8400万个，目前已经挖出6100多万个，现价60美金一个，总市值36.7亿美金，排名第四。</p><p>LTC历史价格走势</p><p>链上交易情况</p><p>LTC等币种链上交易数据对比</p><p>近3个月LTC平均手续费</p><p>LTC链上交易数与交易额相较于BTC、ETH还有不少差距，但考虑到其市值和用户群体规模，以及24小时交易额能够占到总市值的5.51%，并有55822个活跃地址，LTC的链上交易可以说还是相当活跃的，尤其近三个月，从其交易手续费的走势可以看出，链上交易在逐渐活跃并保持着增长。</p><p>LTC分布情况</p><p>LTC分配情况</p><p>前10、100、1000地址持币占比</p><p>LTC的分配情况显示出目前加密货币领域的通病，大量的筹码集中在少数头部的地址当中，前500位地址占据LTC近60%的量，但相较于其他小币种，LTC地址的分配情况已经较为分散，跟大部分主流币的情况差不多，并且这其中包涵了中心化交易所的地址。</p><p>LTC矿池</p><p>LTC矿池份额</p><p>LTC矿池份额占比基本都比较均有，最高的F2Pool占比20.45%，前几大矿池的占比都比较接近，这有利于维护币种的安全和矿工的利益，而全网总共269.77TH/s的算力，相较于BTC 47.31 EH/s和BCH 1.6EH/s还是有一定的差距。 </p><p>LTC最后100个区块的哈希分配</p><p>LTC在Github代码更新频率一直保持不错的情况，最近三个月有所减缓。</p><p>从谷歌趋势可以看出，LTC近一年的热度在主流币当中都是处于较高的位置，而关注LTC的地区主要集中在美洲和欧洲，尤其在美国、加拿大和维瑞内拉。</p><p>结论</p><p>从以上数据基本可以一览LTC整个项目目前的基本情况，从其链活跃程度、分配情况、矿池份额、算力、代码更新、谷歌趋势可以看出，LTC整条链保持良好的运行情况，作为市值排名第四的加密货币，其链上活跃程度、去中心化程度以及谷歌趋势相较于其他主流币种也有不错的表现，但同样，加密货币的通病在其身上也有充分的体现。</p><p>不过，这仅仅是一些表面数据的罗列和展现，下篇我们将会对LTC的通证循环、挖矿机制、支付生态及其落地模块进展做详细的分析和讨论。</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (96, 53, 'zh-CN', '简单易实操的币市绝对收益策略——中低频网格套利', '<p>套利交易简介</p><p>套利交易，又叫对冲交易，遵循“市场中性”原则，即同时进行两笔行情相关、方向相反、数量相当、盈亏相抵的交易。最常见的套利交易发生在满足条件一对标的上，交易时，买入认为被低估的标的，同时卖出被高估的标的，当差价恢复时，平仓出场。本质上，套利交易是交易者选择两个标的，构建投资组合，并以组合内两个标的的差价，作为交易对象，如投资者认为价差较低时，买入/开多价差，价差上涨后平仓获利。投资者关心的是组合内标价格的相互关系，而不是其绝对价格水平，通过其差价的波动来获利，同时避免了价格直接波动的影响。</p><p>套利交易的基本方法</p><p>当我们选择A,B两个产品组成交易对时，我们定义组合的差价 diff = price_A – price_B。当认为diff处于低位时，我们开多diff，diff上涨到合适位置平仓。开多diff，即开多A，同时开空B；平多，即平多A，同时平多B。开空平空同理。下面我们具体举例说明。</p><p>如我们选择OKEx的BTC永续合约和BTC季度合约分别作为A和B，diff = 永续价格 – 季度价格。永续和季度合约各1个BTC保证金。</p><p>套利交易资产组合选择的首要因素是，两交易对价格的强相关性，如我们可以选择OKEx不同期的合约，合约与现货，或OKEx合约与OKCoin现货等。</p><p>另外需要考虑差价的波动范围和平台手续费，一次完整的开仓和平仓，需要进行4笔交易，差价的波动需要足够大以保证足够大的利润空间。</p><p>还有，我们需要观察差价的波动周期，确保交割周期内，差价客户收敛，避免因为在差价回归之前交割，造成亏损。</p><p>根据这些要求，OKEx的BTC永续合约和BTC季度合约是一个很好的套利组合。</p><p>网格交易法</p><p>所谓网格交易法（grid trading method），也称鱼网交易网，秉持的原则是“仓位策略比择时策略更重要 ” 。其基本操作方式就是以某点为基点，每上涨或下跌一定点数挂一定数量空单或多单，设定盈利目标，但不设止损，当价格朝期望方向进展时获利平仓，并在原点位挂同样的买单或卖单。这样布下的这些交易单形成了一张像鱼网样的阵列，在震荡的市场中来回获利。</p><p>从上面简单的原理描述中我们不难看出，网格交易法盈利的核心是“均值回归”，在震荡行情中，网格策略会有非常好的表现。而套利交易目标交易对的差价，天然具有“必然回归”的属性，比如交割合约的价格最终必然回归于现货，永续合约与交割合约的价格同样“必然回归”。因此，网格交易法天然适合用于币市的套利。</p><p>中低频网格套利策略</p><p>我们以OKEx BTC永续合约和BTC季度合约为例，我们定义diff = 永续价格 – 季度价格，下图为diff在2019.7.27-2019.8.27一个月的波动情况，可以看出，diff从+1%左右至-3%左右区间中震荡，中间几次穿过0轴。</p><p>网格的设置和执行：</p><p>以做多网格为例：</p><p>随着价格下跌，每跌至一个格子的价格，我们开一份多仓。随着价格的下跌，我们依次开了买1，买2，买3三份多仓（即在图中买1买2买3三个位置，分别在永续合约开多约30张，并在季度合约开等量空仓）；然后随着价格的回升，我们依次平掉买3，买2，买1三部分仓位（即在图中平买1平买2平买3三个位置，分别平掉永续约所开的30张多仓，并同时平掉季度合约当时所开张数空仓），获利为三个格子的仓位*一个格子差价对应的利润。做空网格同理。</p><p>因为差价存在必然回归到0值的基本假设，因此，差价小于0时，我们执行做多网格，差价大于0时，我们执行做空网格。且基于差价归0假设，开仓后，我们不必做止损，等待价格回归平仓即可。</p><p>风险分析</p><p>理论上，在中低频范畴内使用网格策略进行套利交易属于一种绝对收益模型，中长期看来，可以保证本金完全无风险。但实际操作中，我们仍然需要考虑所选标的特点等实际问题带来的潜在风险。</p><p>单边爆仓风险</p><p>套利交易每笔操作正常为对冲操作，持有等量多空仓位对冲价格波动，但仍可能出现由于价格巨幅波动造成的一边仓位爆仓，爆仓后，另一边持仓失去对冲的保护，会造成策略不可控的价格波动带来的巨大风险。因此，首先要控制总杠杆倍数为相对低的程度，另外，一方亏损较大时，即使划转保证金保护其仓位安全。</p><p>手续费和资金费率</p><p>由于套利交易是通过差价波动来盈利，因此单笔盈利较薄，我们通过中低频操作，较大的格子，来保证每笔盈利足以覆盖交易手续费和永续合约资金费率可能带来的损失。</p><p>合约交割问题</p><p>另外，合约交割时，可能出现差价不回归的问题，因此临近合约交割，我们只平仓不开仓，交割前，主动平掉两边所有仓位。</p><p>总结</p><p>总的来说，网格套利整体风险极低，逻辑简单明了，可以做到无视币价涨跌稳定盈利。同时，选择中低频大网格操作，相对高频而言，手续费不敏感，对没有程序化实现能力的朋友，手动操作亦可执行。</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (97, 54, 'zh-CN', '今日资讯', '<p><span style=\"color: #35384a;\"><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Arial, Microsoft YaHei, \\微软雅黑, \\宋体, Malgun Gothic, Meiryo, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"caret-color: #333333; color: #333333; font-family: Nunito, Montserrat, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.1599999964237213px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"color: #666666; font-family: Arial, Microsoft YaHei, \\微软雅黑, \\宋体, Malgun Gothic, Meiryo, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"caret-color: #333333; color: #333333; font-family: Nunito, Montserrat, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.1599999964237213px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Bekonex</span></span></span>&nbsp;支持30多种法币通过多种支付方式便捷购买比特币、以太坊、USDT等数字货币，最快1分钟内完成交易。</span></p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (98, 55, 'en', 'What is a Fund Transfer?', '<p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">New Features: Funding Account & Trading Account</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p> </o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">To help you manage your funds better, we have launched a new feature under “Account” named “Funding Account”.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">“Funding Account” is just like a bank account which is used to store, receive and send your digital asset to another wallet. All your future deposits and withdrawals will have to go through this account. If you would like to perform trades under different trading zones, you will first have to transfer your funds from “Funding Account” to the respective trading account, such as spot account or futures account.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">“Spot Account” will no longer serve as the main account for handling your deposits and withdrawals. It will, instead, serve as a spot trading account only.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Desktop:</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">How to Manage Funding Account?</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Select “Account > Funding Account” to manage your funds. You may deposit or withdraw funds by using the column on your left. Basic information like the total estimated value of your account and the proportion of owned token will be shown on the page.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p> </o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">How to Start Trading?</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Under “Funding Account”, select “transfer” of the token you wish to trade. Then choose the trading account, amount to complete the transfer.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">You may also click the arrow in the middle to transfer funds from trading account back to “Funding Account”.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p> </o:p></span><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">How to Check My Transfer Record?</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Select “History” to check all deposit, withdrawal, and transfer records.</span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">What is Trading Account?</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">We have now grouped all your trading accounts (i.e. spot account, fiat account, futures account) into a Trading Account. You may transfer funds between your accounts under this tab.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (99, 56, 'en', 'How to Make Cryptocurrency Deposits and Withdraws', '<p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">To deposit or withdraw funds on OKEx, you may go to “Account > Balance”, and select “Deposit” or “Withdraw”</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Deposit</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In the Deposit page, you can change the type of token you wish to deposit in the drop-down list.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:12.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><i><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">IMPORTANT: Send only the specific type of token to the corresponding deposit address.  For example, BTC deposit address only accepts BTC deposits. Sending any other types of token will result in loss of your deposit.</span></i><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">You will be given a deposit address for each type of token.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:12.0000pt;mso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Withdrawal</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">For the safety of your funds, in advance of making any withdrawals, you are required to bind your email address with your account. You may go to “Settings > Security > Verify Email > Show more” to complete the settings.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">To withdraw your funds to other platform, you may go to “Account > Deposit” to perform the action.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><i><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Please check carefully, as the address for each type of token is unique. Withdrawing tokens to an incorrect address can be irreversible and result in loss of funds.</span></i><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p> </o:p></span></p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (100, 57, 'en', 'An Introduction to Cryptocurrency Futures', '<h2 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">What are Futures Contracts?</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Futures contract is an agreement to trade a particular commodity or financial instrument at a predetermined price at a specified time in the future.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In a futures contract, both counter-parties have their obligations and rights.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">For example: Both counter-parties agree on 10 contracts of the delivery of soybean at the price $5000. Then the buyer has an obligation and right to buy 10 tons of soybean at the price $5000 on a specific date. At the same time, the seller has an obligation and right to sell 10 tons of soybean at the price $5000 on the same date. The contract that represents the obligations and rights of both counter-parties is a futures contract.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">But most of the time, investors do not ask for physical delivery. Instead, before the contract expires, which is also prior to the delivery day, investors will close the position to profit from the the price difference.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h2 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">How to Trade Futures Contracts?</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">1. According to the BTC price movement, user may choose to open long or short position of different delivery dates. </span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Currently,  supports weekly, bi-weekly and quarterly contracts.Weekly contracts will be settled on the imminent Friday.Bi-weekly contracts will be settled on next Friday.Quarterly contracts will be settled on the last Friday of March, June, September and December.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p> </o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">2. Enter the Quantity and Price. </span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">When creating an order, the margin required is the value of the filled contract in BTC equivalent divided by the leverage multiplier. Order can only be placed when the account equity balance is larger than or equal to the margin.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p> </o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">3. Margin</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">When creating a new futures account, user will have to choose the margin mode before trading. Different margin modes have different margin formulae and risk management systems. User may switch the margin mode when he/she does not have any opened position and order (margin of all contract = zero).</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In cross-margin mode, the risks and profits of all holding positions will be shared together. Under this mode, the minimum margin ratio for opening a position is 100%.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In fixed-margin mode, the margins and profits of each position will be isolated. User can only open a position when the equity balance is larger than the initial margin. However, the initial margin for each contract might be different.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">4. Once the order is filled, user will hold the respective positions (long or short). </span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In cross-margin mode, the equity balance of futures account has to be larger than 10% of the holding positions for 10x leverage contracts; 20% for 20x leverage contracts. In fixed-margin mode, the UPL varies based on the latest market price, but the margin remains the same as initial margin. Once the margin ratio drops to or below 10% (10x) / 20% (20x), our system will take over and force-liquidate the position(s).</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">5. Position</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">User may open more or close position(s) anytime to take profit / stop loss.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p> </o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">6. Realized profit & loss</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">On the delivery day, all opened positions will be closed at market price(USD). The profit / loss will be transferred to the futures account under “Realized profit & loss”.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">7. Delivery</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">After delivery, the societal losses will be covered proportionally by the accounts with realised profits from the same contract.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">8. Transferred</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">After settlement, all realized profit and loss will be transferred to the equity balance.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">9. Ending</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The existing contract ends. New contracts will be launched</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (101, 58, 'en', 'How to complete BigWinPro Verification on STAI', '<p>How to complete BigWinPro Verification on STAI<br data-mce-bogus=\"1\"></p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Note： 1. Please prepare your passport in advance and record the verification video according to the instructions. 2. We will guide you through the process step by step. Please strictly follow the instructions. 3. We suggest you to double check the video after recording. Please record again if you found any problem. Otherwise, the verification may fail. 4. The video size is about 20MB. We suggest you to perform the verification with Wi-Fi connection for best result.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Note：</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">1. Please prepare your passport in advance and record the verification video according to the instructions.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">2. We will guide you through the process step by step. Please strictly follow the instructions.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">3. We suggest you to double check the video after recording. Please record again if you found any problem. Otherwise, the verification may fail.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">4. The video size is about 20MB. We suggest you to perform the verification with Wi-Fi connection for best result.</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (102, 59, 'en', 'Event Arbitrage: How to Trade Halvings', '<p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><i><span class=\"17\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Thomas Tse</span></i><i><span class=\"17\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><br></span></i><i><span class=\"17\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Head Quantitative Strategist</span></i><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">With the next </span><a href=\"https://www.okex.me/academy/en\"><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bitcoin</span></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> halving expected to happen under a month (May 12, 2020), a significant number of users believe that this will create a bullish run for BTC as halving decreases its inflation. In this article, we’ll use historical data to explore how to trade halvings from an events arbitrage perspective.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Looking at historical data</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In April 2020, we experienced halvings for both Bitcoin Cash (BCH) and Bitcoin SV (BSV) on Apr 8 and Apr 10 respectively. Let’s look at their price graphs against BTC only so as to remove the noise created by market movements:</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">We can observe that the price peaks on the halving date. As a quantitative trader, I believe the price of assets in the short-term is driven by supply and demand. The fundamental aspect of decreased inflation that causes price increase can be ignored in the short-term. We can imagine that the price is at the highest point when the market is sentiment is high due to all the news surrounding the halving. Take a look at the Google Trend screenshots below. It shows that the search for BCH and BSV peaked right at the time of halving, meaning demand is at its highest. Therefore, in theory, we can buy the rumor and sell the news.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Backtesting the Long Short Strategy</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">We can see that the Google Trend usually begins to rise about 3 days before halving, peaks on the halving date, and then goes down after halving. Using the past halving data of LTC (halved on Aug 5, 2019), BCH and BSV, we can propose a simple trade to </span><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">long before halving, short on the halving date, and unwind the final position 3 days after halving</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">We can perform 3 trades against the BTC quote pair to remove noise from the market: Buy ~1 BTC of the halving coin 3 days prior to halving, short ~1 BTC on the halving date, then unwind 3 days after halving to net a total of 33.84% return, with an average 11.28% return on each trade.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Example:</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The total return will be around 0.3384 BTC (33.84%), with an average return of 11.28%.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">How to trade the upcoming BTC halving</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">This simple back test shows that there is alpha when you “buy rumor, sell news” for small-cap coins. However, applying this to trade BTC is different and there is no easy way to hedge the market. In the examples above, we are essentially delta flat as we are constantly buying or selling BTC against the halving coin. But for a similar BTC trade, we need to either take delta by trading it against USD or USDT with OKEx Margin Lending or USDT swap; or alternatively hedge it with ETH. It will be up to traders themselves to determine which is the best cause of action.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h4 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:21.7500pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Conclusion</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h4><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Today we looked at an event arbitrage trading strategy to long a halving coin before halving and then short it right after halving. To summarize, the theory behind is that due to the heated discussion and news on halving, the demand for that coin will increase prior to the event; but as the news die down after it halves, the buying pressure is gone and the coin price would drop. We’ve backtested the strategy on 3 coins against BTC to remain delta neutral. It is now up to traders to decide whether we apply this trading logic to the upcoming BTC halving in May.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Halving dates for different coins:</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: 宋体; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\">Di</span><i><span class=\"17\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">sclaimer: This material should not be taken as the basis for making investment decisions, nor be construed as a recommendation to engage in investment transactions. Trading digital assets involves significant risk and can result in the loss of your invested capital. You should ensure that you fully understand the risk involved and take into consideration your level of experience, investment objectives and seek independent financial advice if necessary.</span></i><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (103, 60, 'en', 'Zero basic to learn analysis of Bitcoin | 2-Candlestick Line and its structure', '<p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">There is a trend of rising and falling, reading the price language;</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">There is a signal to buy and sell, and bid farewell to feeling the deal.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In the last episode, we have introduced Candlestick Line and its structure. But why do we need to understand Candlestick Line?</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In this video, we will talk about its evolution and meaning.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Let’s first look at how the Candlestick Line evolved in successive price changes.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">This horizontal line shows the opening price and the closing price are the same. It is called a “4-price Doji”.  It often occurs at the market opening moment, or during a period with minimal trading volume, or when the price goes up and then finally goes back to where it started.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Price changes when the market becomes active, a small candle with a short entity is formed. The green part indicates the price goes up, and it is called a up candle; where the red part indicates the price goes down, it is called down candle.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">When the market becomes more active, the Down candle and Up candle will be longer.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">And when the transaction period becomes extremely active, the Down candle and Up candle will be even longer.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">So how is the shadow formed?</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Let’s go back to when the market just opened.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The price falls gradually.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">And when the price falls to a certain price, a group of actively buying investors gradually appear in the market, pushing the price up step by step and forming a lower shadow line. And as shown in the figure, the entity becomes shorter with a lower shadow line, it is usually called the “hammer line”.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">When the candle entity becomes a thin line, we call it the cross.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">As the buying power becomes stronger and stronger, the price gradually rises, forming two bullish Up candles.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">When the price rises to a certain height, a group of actively selling investors appear in the market. The price is slowly suppressed, forming a Hachure, as shown in the figure.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The candle entity on the right is small, with a Hachure, it is usually called the “reverse hammer line”.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">When the selling volume gradually increases, the price continues to fall to the point that the final closing price was the same as the opening price. As shown in the figure, the K line on the left that looks like a cross, is called the “cross star line”, and the right picture is called the “Gravestone Doji” because it resembles a gravestone. It can also be called the “inverted T-line”.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">We have learned a lot of candlesticks after going through their variations. How many kinds of K lines are there?</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">And how should these candlesticks be classified?</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">As shown, we arrange all kinds of candlesticks in an orderly manner. ️</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> There is a total of 42 kinds by multiplying the rows and columns. We will first explain the meaning of the length of the candle entity.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The first row shows green Up candles with a short entity, implying that the bullish strength is weak.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The second row shows green Up candles with a longer entity, meaning that the bullish strength is strong.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The third row shows green Up candle with a very long entity, which means that the bullish strength has an absolute advantage.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In the fourth row, the bodies are in the form of thin lines. They are collectively called the “Doji lines”, meaning that the buying and selling power are fierce and evenly matched.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The fifth row shows the red Down candles with a short entity, implying the bearish strength is weak.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The sixth row shows the red Down candles with a longer entity, implying a stronger bearish strength.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In the seventh row shows the red Down candle with a very long entity, implying the bearish strength has an absolute advantage. Next, we are going to unveil the meaning of the length of the upper and lower shadow lines.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In the first column, there is no upper and lower shadow line on the K line. We usually call it the “bald head”, which means that the situation is one-sided. The positive line indicates bullish strength and the negative line indicates strong bulls.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The second column, only the lower shadow line, it looks like the candle has no long hair, so it is often called “bald”. It implies there is support from the buying side. The longer the lower shadow line, the stronger the support.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In the third column, the K line has only the Hachure which is usually called “barefoot”. It implies there is a resistance, the longer the upper shadow line, the stronger the resistance.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In the fourth column, the lengths of the upper and lower shadow lines are almost equal, meaning that the support and resistance are both equal.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In the fifth column, the lower shadow line is longer than the upper shadow line, meaning that the lower support is greater than the upper resistance.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In the sixth column, the upper shadow line is longer than the lower shadow line, meaning that the upper resistance is greater than the lower support.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Arranging the K lines of without arrays constitutes the price chart we often see. The screenshot is from the price chart of the BTC/USDT in the OKEx currency trading area.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Here comes the end of our section, we will share about observing the Chart regular arrangement and predicting the future price rise and fall in the next video.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p> </o:p></span></p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (104, 61, 'en', 'Zero basic to learn analysis of Bitcoin | 1-Candlestick Line', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">There is a trend of rising and falling, reading the price language;</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">There is a signal to buy and sell, and bid farewell to feeling the deal.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Today we are going to learn the most basic element in technical analysis: the candlestick line. Candlestick line is the most common price marking method nowadays.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Let’s take a look at how the price works in the market during the day.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">When not processed by the candlestick line notation, the price of an investment product is such that countless prices are combined to form a seemingly erratic curve. It looks a little chaotic, isn’t it?</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Next, let’s do a simple technical analysis process, mark the key price points</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Opening price、closing price、 highest price、 lowest price.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">We filter out the confusing price changes and draw them into a line chart.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">As shown in the picture, does this look much clearer?</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Can you say it in a simpler way?</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Certainly. Let’s have a look at the candlestick line chart.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">As shown in the figure, the opening price, closing price, lowest price and highest price are shifted to a vertical line.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The candlestick line entity is formed between the opening price and the closing price. We use a thicker line.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The entity is between the highest price and the lowest price. We use thin lines to form the  hachure and lower shadow lines.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">If the closing price is lower than the opening price, we mark the entity in red, indicating that the price has fallen during that time, usually called the exterior circle.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The closing price is higher than the opening price.,we use green to mark the entity, indicating that the price rises during the period, usually called the inner circle. (Of course, some markets will use the opposite color to mark the candlestick line up and down.)</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">When we connect the candlestick lines of each day, we will see our common candlestick line pattern.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Each red or green candlestick line in the figure represents the price change data for the day.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">A day’s price trend can be expressed by a candlestick line, then one minute, one hour, one week?</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">According to the time range of statistical price changes, we divide the K-line into different periods. This is how many one-minute candlestick lines are connected, and this is how many “one-week  candlestick lines” are connected.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Cycles are very flexible and can be divided into minutes, hours, days, weeks or months.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">What role does the candlestick line play in the investment market?</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">When a specific candlestick line shape or a specific candlestick line combination appears, a specific price trend will probably occur.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Because prices include all market behaviour, history will be strikingly similar.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Then we will share the method of predicting future price rise and fall by observing the regularity of candlestick line arrangement.</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (105, 62, 'en', 'Zero basic to learn analysis of Bitcoin | 4-Bearish Candlestick Patterns', '<h1 class=\"single-title\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 40px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Zero basic to learn analysis of Bitcoin | 4-Bearish Candlestick Patterns</h1><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">There is a trend of rising and falling, reading the price language;</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">There is a signal to buy and sell, and bid farewell to feeling the deal.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Today, we’re going to learn about the Bearish Candlestick Patterns.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The appearance of the evening star indicates that the bull trend has come to an end and an adjustment is coming.Let’sstart with the Evening Star.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">What is an Evening Star? As shown in the red line.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The evening star is a bearish candlestick pattern which consist of three candles: a large white candlestick, a small-bodied candle, and a red candle. An evening star demonstrates a unique characteristic: the closing price of the last candle must be lower than the first candle for at least 50%.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">We can even determine the bearish level of the market by looking at the closing price of the last candle. As you can see in the chart, the red candle’s closing price has just exceeded the 50% level. This indicates that the bearish trend is comparatively weak. If the red candle’s closing price is close to or the same as the white candle’s opening price, it means that the bearish trend is comparatively strong;the red candle’s closing price is significantly lower than the white candle’s opening price, it means that the bearish trend is very strong.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">In everyday trading markets, an evening star may not be so obvious as you can recognize from text books. Here are some examples we found in the past:</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">In the first figure, you can see the middle section is formed by two small candlesticks. Let’s move them back to the real-life trading chart. After a strong price surge, an evening star is seen at the high level, then we immediately see a price correction pattern.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The second figure is taken from OKEx – a 2hr BTC/USD chart. This may not be a perfect example as the middle candle is not significantly small. However, we can still see an evening star pattern and the price falls immediately after the pattern is formed.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">In the third figure, two small-bodied candles formed the middle section.  We can also see that the red candle’s closing price is significantly lower than the white candle’s opening price. The price tumbles after continuous oscillations.Sometimes, the evening star may appear multiple times in a short time. In this BTC/USDT bearish trend, we see two evening stars when the price rallies back up, and falls immediately after.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The second one we will learn about is Bearish Engulfing.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">A bearish engulfing pattern consists of a white candlestick followed by a large red candlestick that “engulfs” the smaller white candle.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">But how can we determine the bearish level if we see such pattern?</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">In the first figure, the red candle barely engulfs the white candle, meaning the bearish trend is weak. In the second figure, the red candle’s closing price is significantly lower than the white candle’s opening price, the length of the red candle is almost twice of the white candle, meaning that the bearish trend is strong. In the third figure, the red candle engulfs multiple white candles at a time, indicating that the bearish trend is extremely strong.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Now, let’s look at some real-life examples.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">As shown in the chart.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The first figure is a LTC/USDT day chart from OKEx. After a price surge, we can see a large red candle engulfing many white candles, and a strong bearish trend follows.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The second figure is an ETH/USDT 2-hour chart from OKEx. After the ETH price rallies back up to a new high, a bearish engulfing pattern is seen, and the bearish trend continues.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The third figure is an EOS/USDT 6-hour chart from OKEx. After a continuous price surge, a bearish engulfing pattern is formed, and a strong bearish trend appears.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The last one we will learn about is the Tower Top.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">A tower top pattern is comprised of a normal or large white candle at the left, several small candles, usually more than 5, in the middle, and a normal or large red candle at the right. As you can see, it looks exactly like a tower top in the chart.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">A tower top often forms after the closing price of the last red candle is lower than the body of the first white candle by 50%. A tower top is a reversal pattern, it indicates a reversal of the bearish trend. This reflects a gradual exhaustion of buyers before the sellers forcefully regain control.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">We can also determine the bearish level of the market by looking at the closing price of the last red candle.As shown in the figure, if the red candle’s closing price barely exceeds the 50% level, the bearish trend will be comparatively weak. But if the closing price is close to the white candle’s opening price, the bearish trend will be stronger. And if the closing price is significantly lower than the white candle’s opening price, the bearish trend will be very strong.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Let’s take a look at some real-life examples.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">This figure is taken from a BTC/USDT 6-hr chart at OKEx. We can see long shadows attached to the small candlesticks. But this phenomenon doesn’t affect the tower top structure, the BTC market sees a strong bearish pattern afterwards, the price falls to a new low.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The second figure shows the spot ACC/USDT 12-hr chart at OKEx. The middle section of the tower top is not formed by unusually small candles, and we can see a larger fluctuation level. After the pattern is formed, ACC price tumbles sharply.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Let’s have a review of what we learn today:</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The first is an evening star, meaning that darkness is upon us. The second is the bearish engulfing, indicating a bear run coming. The last one is the tower top, reflecting the gradual exhaustion of buyers.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Here comes the end of our section, we will show you the importance of the various Candlestick Line combinations position</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (106, 63, 'en', 'Tokenized Bitcoins, Exchanges Under Fire and TRX as a Security: Crypto News of the Week', '<h2 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bittrex and Poloniex added to class-action lawsuit against Bitfinex and Tether</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">“In reality, Tether issued billions of USDT to itself with no U.S. dollar backing— simply creating the USDT out of thin air. Tether hid that fact by ‘selling’ newly issued USDT to Bitfinex, a crypto-exchange that was secretly owned and operated by the same individuals who owned and operated Tether. Because Bitfinex and Tether were essentially the same, Tether could simply transfer newly issued USDT into its account on Bitfinex without receiving U.S. dollars in exchange, as was required from genuine customers.”</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bittrex and Poloniex, meanwhile, are alleged to have knowingly participated in the USDT printing scheme by transferring large sums of knowingly-unbacked tethers.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Key Takeaways</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The amended class-action lawsuit against Tether and associated firms is growing, with new exchanges being added as defendants. The potential for other cryptocurrency exchanges to be added may exist.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">If the lawsuit is won, shockwaves would undoubtedly be felt throughout the entire industry and the price of </span><a href=\"https://www.okex.me/academy/en\"><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Bitcoin</span></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> would likely react negatively.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h2 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Tokenized bitcoins on Ethereum outnumbering Lightning and Liquid</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">When it comes to off-chain Bitcoin transactions, Ethereum-based projects like WBTC and imBTC are currently the most popular choices — topping well-known Bitcoin-based projects like Lightning Network and Liquid. </span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">As reported by CoinDesk, there are </span><a href=\"https://www.coindesk.com/ethereum-has-become-bitcoins-top-off-chain-destination\"><u><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">70 percent</span></u></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> more bitcoins on these Ethereum projects than then on the Bitcoin sidechains mentioned above. Furthermore, the tokenized Bitcoin supply has grown 330 percent in 2020.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Key takeaways</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">More options for off-chain Bitcoin transactions provide more choices for users, facilitating adoption.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Ethereum’s diversity of use cases is illustrated by the growing number of tokenized bitcoins. It stands to reason we will continue to see use cases grow.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h2 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">“Crypto Mom” Hester Peirce nominated for second SEC term</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Hester Peirce, known by some in crypto as “Crypto Mom” for her advocacy of the industry — has been </span><a href=\"https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/ten-nominations-one-withdrawal-sent-senate-2/\"><u><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">nominated</span></u></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> to serve a second term as a member of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) until 2025.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Peirce has historically been </span><a href=\"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/sec-commissioner-supports-creation-of-a-non-exclusive-safe-harbour-for-tokens-at-suss-convergence-forum-300896187.html\"><u><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">a strong proponent</span></u></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> of blockchain technology and </span><a href=\"https://www.sec.gov/news/public-statement/peirce-dissent-34-83723\"><u><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">opposed</span></u></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> the SEC’s stringent stance on cryptocurrencies.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Key takeaways</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo3;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Peirce has been the only member of the SEC to voice opposition to </span><a href=\"https://www.okex.com/academy/en/bitcoin-bandwagoning-an-examination-of-institutional-investment-in-crypto?channelFlag=ACECO1500807\"><u><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Bitcoin ETF application denials</span></u></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">. Should her second term be approved, the likelihood of ever seeing such an exchange-traded fund is, at the very least, not damaged.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo3;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Peirce has also argued for self-regulation and a safe harbor from the SEC for projects with decentralized tokens.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h2 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Europol sets sights on Bitcoin privacy tool Wasabi Wallet</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Europol is reportedly targeting privacy-focused, open-source Bitcoin wallet, Wasabi Wallet. </span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The news was first reported by </span><a href=\"https://www.coindesk.com/europol-bitcoin-privacy-wasabi-wallet\"><u><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">CoinDesk</span></u></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> after a European Union’s law enforcement agency’s “law enforcement only” report on the wallet leaked on Telegram. The leak was later verified by Europol’s press department.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Europol’s European Cybercrime Centre (EC3) cited data from Chainalysis, the leading blockchain analysis company in the space. The report states:</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><br></span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><br></span><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">“According to [Chainalysis], over the last three weeks, BTC in the amount of nearly 50 million USD were deposited into Wasabi with almost 30% coming from dark web markets. This is a significant amount, relatively speaking, given the dark web transactions are estimated to have only 1% share of total transactions.”</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Key takeaways</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo4;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Though it does not necessarily infer specific action will be taken by Europol, the report clearly illustrates how Bitcoin privacy tools are on law enforcement’s radar.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo4;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Privacy tools obscure data on </span><a href=\"https://www.okex.com/academy/en/can-crypto-be-private-bitcoins-public-ledger-in-an-age-of-increased-surveillance\"><u><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Bitcoin’s distributed public ledger</span></u></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">, but regulators may step in.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><h2 style=\"margin-top:30.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">TRON’s TRX strongly resembles a security, says industry council</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Crypto Rating Council (CRC) has unofficially deemed Tron’s, Nervos’ and Polkadot’s respective tokens as facing a higher likelihood of being deemed securities under U.S. securities law, according to a mid-April rating list obtained by </span><a href=\"https://www.theblockcrypto.com/post/64569/crypto-ratings-preliminary-scores-trx-dot-ckb\"><u><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Block</span></u></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The unpublished rating list in question reportedly assigned a score to each token of 4.75 out of 5.00, which means that they strongly resemble securities.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Key takeaways</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo5;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The CRC was founded by Coinbase, Circle, Genesis Capital, and other high-profile crypto firms to provide clarity on regulatory issues surrounding cryptocurrencies. Thus, its assessment does not mean that TRX and others are actually securities in the eyes of regulators — only that the council has determined that they resemble them.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo5;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">If the SEC was to hypothetically heed the CRC’s assessment, the Tron, Nervos and Polkadot ecosystems would likely undergo a tumultuous experience.</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (107, 64, 'en', 'Gear Up for the Cryptocurrency Fed Meeting', '<p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Whether you are a crypto trader or a traditional financial market participant, the upcoming US Federal Reserve interest rate meeting is something that you cannot afford to ignore. The Fed’s interest rate decision will certainly be a key driver of all asset classes such as equities and commodities, even crypto. The month-end meeting is especially important because we may see our first rate-cut this year.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"17\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Rate Cut is Expected</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18.5pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">As the global economic mood sours, the continuation of the US economic expansion is questionable, and global trade tensions remained high, markets are expected the FOMC to cut the rates by 25 basis points next week. St. Louis Fed President James Bullard told Bloomberg </span><a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-07-21/powell-preference-and-fomc-split-support-quarter-point-july-cut\"><u><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">that</span></u></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">, “I’d like to go 25 basis points at the upcoming meeting,”, New York Fed President John Williams went even further, calling for a more aggressive policy move. According to CME’s FedWatch, US rates futures implied traders positioned for an 80% chance that the FOMC may lower its rate by a quarter-point at its July policy meeting.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:宋体;font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;\">(Source: CME Group)</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"17\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Why Gold Matters?</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18.5pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In the background of a weaker global economic growth, gold has been back in the spotlight. The precious metal was one of the worst-performing asset classes last year, but it managed to make a comeback in May 2019, topped $1440 level just this month.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The latest CFTC’s weekly Commitments of Traders report shows that, the net positions for “non-commercial” (speculative) traders in US gold futures markets still near an all-time high, implying market sentiment remains positive for gold.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Traditionally, lower interest rates reduce the opportunity cost of holding non-yielding gold and pressure the dollar. If the July rate cut is materialized and the expectation of more rate cuts remained intact, this could help gold bulls to gain more solid ground, extending the momentum of the bullion rally.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"17\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">What Gold and Risk Appetite Can Tell Us About BTC?</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18.5pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Gold and BTC have continued to show high correlation during their recent rallies, we haven’t seen such a high degree of synchronization since 2016. The following chart shows that gold and BTC were mostly in an inverse correlation in Q4 last year to H1 of this year, but their relationship started to change in late June.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:宋体;font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;\">Gold and bitcoin </span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">If gold and JPY were the traditional safe-haven assets, then BTC perhaps could be considered as a new kind of risk-aversion tool. Let’s have a look at USDJPY, it’s one of the key risk sentiment barometers in the market, capital flows into JPY when global risk sentiment is high. When we look at USDJPY and BTC together, the cryptocurrency seems to play exactly the same role as JPY. On top of that, considering the slowing of the US economic growth, and the growing risk of long-term stagnation elsewhere, that will limit the possibility of the Fed to increase interest rates, causing additional pressure to USD, JPY and BTC could benefit from that.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:宋体;font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:0.0000pt;\">USDJPY and Bitcoin </span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"17\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Conclusion</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 18.5pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Fed July meeting is certainly important for all market participants. The road to rate hike seems to come to an end, at least in the near term. The case of medium to long term bearish of USD remains strong, safe-haven assets such as gold and JPY are expected to continue on high demand due to unresolved trade tensions and economic uncertainties. Referencing the correlations with gold and USDJPY, BTC could also benefit from this global risk-building environment.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">More traditional market players have put BTC under their radar, as the tie between the crypto world and traditional financial markets is getting closer every day. The medium to long term BTC bullish case remains solid.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><i><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Disclaimer: This material should not be taken as the basis for making investment decisions, nor be construed as a recommendation to engage in investment transactions. Trading digital assets involves significant risk and can result in the loss of your invested capital. You should ensure that you fully understand the risk involved and take into consideration your level of experience, investment objectives and seek independent financial advice if necessary.</span></i><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (108, 65, 'en', 'Value, Price, and Cost: How Blockchain Changes Business Value', '<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">When the market crashes before your eyes, it is tough to imagine what will come next. While blockchain technology itself is flourishing with governments, public services, and some private companies, public blockchain businesses are desperately looking for a sign of hope remaining in the market. However, this may also be the perfect time to talk about the real value that blockchain technology and this market can offer. Can blockchain technology bring change in value for business and consumers? If so, how much value to whom? Can it suggest a competitive business model compared the incumbent business? Let’s talk about the new type of value that blockchain business — more specifically, the emergence of public blockchain businesses — may bring from three perspectives of value, price, and cost.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;\">Cost: Who is Picking Up the Bill?</span></p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Let us remind ourselves of the most basic framework of value, price, and cost. Price and cost determine a firm’s profit while price and value yield a consumer’s surplus.</p><div class=\"wp-block-image\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 14px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(31, 34, 54); font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(79, 86, 105); font-size: 16px;\">From the service provider’s perspective, reducing cost or (and) raising price would increase its profit. Many say that blockchain technology reduce the cost of running a business, but this argument may be controversial. When it comes to the cost of operating centralized data server or network, blockchain technology does save such cost. The unexpected cost, however, may arise in providing stable service quality with several nodes participating in the blockchain network — as we all know, blockchain is not a technology that features superior efficiency as centralized network. As seen in multiple projects, the ‘inefficiency cost’ may be even higher than the cost saved by using blockchain technology as the business grows. Vitalik Buterin, the founder of Ethereum, said, “the medium scale computing cost of Amazon’s EC2 (that features elastic compute cloud service) is $0.04 per an hour, while the cost of doing the same task in Ethereum is about $13.40 per 200 milliseconds, which is 1.4 million times more expensive than that of Amazon.” [1] This shows the current gap in efficiency that the blockchain industry may have to catch up with. As the business grows, limited scalability and inefficiency cost of blockchain even get worse, whereas the centralized network server enjoy the economy of scale and incur less cost per consumer. We thus cannot simply argue the total cost of running blockchain business will be much lower than before.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(79, 86, 105); font-size: 16px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;\"> However, what is truly striking about blockchain business is that consumers, not firms, are usually the ones who pick up the bill for such cost.</span></figure></div><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">In traditional business model, this is how it works — a company builds and maintains centralized network server capable of handling many requests from users. The cost for operating such network is covered by a firm, and the profit of serving users comes next. In a blockchain network, however, firms are not responsible for processing user requests, but the ‘voluntarily participating nodes’ are. And users are charged for the cost of rewarding them. For example, when people use a DApp based on Ethereum network, they need pay the reward for nodes to process their requests either in token issued by the DApp or ETH — meaning that the firm is no longer the only one who pays the bill to get the network running.</p><h2 id=\"fbcb\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;\">Price: From Unseen to Seen</span></h2><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Price includes the cost plus a firm’s profit. Let’s think about how much we have paid to use IT services that we use every day. It is surprising that the very idea of ‘paying to use a service’ is quite unfamiliar in current IT business. Once connected to the internet, you do not have to pay a single penny everytime you send an email with Google, or check your friends’ photos on Facebook. Except for premium membership plans to skip the advertisement or to expand the cloud storage, most IT firms do not charge users for using their services. It does not mean these services are entirely free of charge — in return, users need to hand control over their data to service providers and advertisers, who are the primary revenue source of business. <span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;\">It is no surprise that some IT giants are criticized for misusing user data when it is simply an ‘invisible price tag’ put on their services.</span> Welcome to the world of ‘sign up for free and use our service’ that we live in.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">In blockchain-based services, however, a price tag becomes more visible. And providing user data to use a service is now strictly separated from paying to use it. It is the user, not service provider, who can solely manage and claim the ownership of user data within a blockchain network. Some blockchain businesses even enable their users to ‘sell’ their data to earn tokens or to pay for using services. A question still remains whether blockchain-based services that put a visible price tag on may come shocking or reasonable to mass consumers who are used to what seems free. Several use cases will be able to answer this question soon.</p><h2 id=\"8e98\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;\">Value: Philosophy Over Practicality?</span></h2><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Among the framework, ‘value’ is the most tricky part to discuss in blockchain business. The value for firms is often defined as their profit, bufor consumers it is more complicated. In simple words, a value is about ‘what makes consumers want to buy a product/service.’ We often encounter with advertisement phrases of blockchain services such as ‘take more control of your privacy’ or ‘more transparent and decentralized transaction’ whereas traditional advertisements used to stress how fast, cheap or convenient it is to use specific services. So, here are some questions that may follow. Would consumers be willing to use blockchain services while compromising efficiency and prompt customer services? Would values proposed by blockchain business such as privacy and resistance to centralized authority be powerful enough to attract mass consumer pool?</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">They say good cannot exist without evil. In blockchain industry, such concepts have been crystal clear since the beginning — decentralization is good whereas centralization is not. Many blockchain business models often get feedback such as ‘It is not decentralized enough’ or ‘Don’t you think your service is way too centralized to be called as blockchain service?’ while a few comments said, ‘It is not practical enough.’ As we have seen in numerous failures of social business, stressing the good cause easily ignores whether it can actually win consumer’s choice over other options. We have learned many lessons that tell us philosophy alone cannot get this industry far. Everybody loves good company, but only when it can provide people with a good reason to be its consumers. Some say the token economy and philosophy that lies underneath can magically allure the consumers in pursuit of the financial reward. However, it lacks real-life evidence or use cases. We have to face that most token economy has served investors, not consumers. We also have witnessed the philosophy of decentralization being tampered with a very few visible hands. It is easy to lose one’s faith in philosophy, but in practicality, it is not. <span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;\">Only when blockchain business does not compromise the practicality of its service, the philosophy can be catered to consumers as a final touch.</span></p><h2 id=\"62e6\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;\">Moving Beyond Competitors</span></h2><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Many wonder if up-and-coming blockchain business can beat its giant competitors. Figure 2 sums up the ideal scenario for the value, price, and cost framework of blockchain business versus its competitor — the cost and price become lower with more consumer’s surplus, which eventually yields more value created in total than its competitors. Although no one can tell if this ideal scenario will turn into reality, it may be controversial that the firm’s profitability of blockchain business was depicted lower than its competitors. But for now, let’s stick to its motto — ‘less rents for middlemen,’ because firms themselves are the middlemen between the nodes of the network and end users. And of course, this figure is just for brief comparison and the specific portions of cost, price and value in the framework may vary upon company to company.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">As of now, it seems like a tough game to win — all three perspectives of value, price, and cost tell a gloomy forecast about the competition with existing firms. Inefficiency cost is way too high, consumers are used to ‘free’ services, and whether the philosophy of blockchain can appeal to mass consumers is in question. Let’s look at the bright side of this uncertainty — with ‘Innovator’s Dilemma,’ a theory suggested by Clayton Christensen in his book titled ‘The Innovator’s Dilemma: When New Technologies Cause Great Firms to Fail.’ This theory illustrated how new technology can disrupt the incumbent market and even cause some of the giants to go out of business. The book described the traits of ‘disruptive technologies’, which change the fundamental value proposition in the market and cause a drastic and sudden paradigm shift which strongest and biggest players often fail to adapt to. If we define blockchain technology as disruptive, it may be growing into an entirely different paradigm, even without competing with current IT giants. No wonder this theory argues that disruptive technology initially offers poorer performance with less capacities than existing solutions. Although the value, price, and cost framework may not tell a bright future of blockchain business, there may be a potential of blockchain business that we cannot see just yet in the paradigm that we live in. We also need to focus on how it already cracked the small part of the way people think. A lot more people have started to notice the ‘inappropriate’ amount of middlemen rents or problems associated with centralized business and economy. <span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;\">Even when the blockchain technology fails to solve these problems and vanishes in the air, what is left behind will last and accelerate the emergence of the next disruption that actually works. </span>Well, let’s keep our hopes high.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: \"SF Pro Text\", \"SF Pro Icons\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><a href=\"https://www.okex.me/academy/en\" class=\"seo-words\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; text-decoration-line: none; user-select: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105) !important;\">Blockchain</a> technology itself does not come along with the ‘proper’ business model or the value framework. This technology merely provides an environment which new business models should adapt to. No one can ever predict how long it will take to for blockchain hype to turn into actual business success. And blockchain technology may not promise us the most lucrative business in human history. One certain fact is that, however, it has showed us the possibility of new normal by disrupting the world of centralized business where maximizing firm’s profits used to be considered a virtue. That is the hope this industry should always stick to through the rough time.</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (109, 66, 'en', 'Lessons from the Crypto-Tsunami', '<p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">As 2018 has now ended, there is a plethora of both prediction and “year in review” commentaries. Across these articles, there is a lot being written about the wreckage left by the crypto tsunami, where crypto surged to meteoric heights in 2017, followed by a brutal bear market in 2018. In 2017 we witnessed tales of incredible wealth and forecasts of world changing technologies. In 2018, we saw both positive and negative stories. On the positive side, adoption continues to increase and many household names have announced plans to enter the market. At the same time, there have been many reports about regulatory actions, cases of fraud, and, of course, the disastrous results of imprudent investments made by investors.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">One of the most important lessons the industry should learn is that there are reasons behind many of the negative stories, including the excessive greed, fraud and organized market manipulation that occurred. The non-financial background of many participants helped create a culture where “caveat emptor” was considered acceptable, while, at the same time, those running most crypto markets had little experience with financial market principles such as best execution or fair and orderly markets. With that backdrop the crypto market developed rapidly as the allure of a new technology sparked the imaginations of investors, with an accelerated cycle of greed and fear as a result.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">2017–2018 was, in many ways, quite similar to the 1990s dotcom bubble. In addition to a new technology that promised disruption of many industries, it featured rapid price appreciation of the major assets and even larger price moves among smaller assets. In fact, much of the behavior in the ICO market closely resembled stories from the over the counter (OTC) equity market, such as those chronicled in the movie “The Wolf of Wall Street”. (This similarity is important to understand for regulators; being securities didn’t protect investors in thousands of cases in the 1990s, so it would be foolish to assume it would have prevented a thing in the ICO craze. Fraud is a crime and needs to be punished, but there is little reason to strangle a nascent industry when doing so)</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">To put all of this in perspective, I would like to highlight 4 important lessons learned last year, along with our perspective:</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">There is enormous investment demand from the global public for early stage technologies</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">For investors, easy money is a siren song</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">$$$s attract opportunists, which, in turn, will attract a regulatory response</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Basic principles of financial markets should not be ignored</span><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Let’s examine each of these in turn:</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">There is massive public demand to invest in early stage technology</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">: As SEC Chairman Clayton has observed, the capital markets have a major problem with attracting new public companies. </span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> while the amount of capital injected into private companies from venture capital and private equity funds has increased significantly. This combination has effectively prevented individual investors from being able to participate in early stage investments in the equity markets. Thus, it is not surprising that, presented with what appeared to be the ability to invest in potentially valuable blockchain projects, many investors jumped at the chance. Despite little more than basic descriptions of ideas, often without real business plans or operational products, companies were able to raise billions of dollars.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The global nature of these offerings, meanwhile, presents a double-edged sword for capital markets in the U.S. On the one hand, the market structure of digital assets promises significant efficiencies to better connect investors and entrepreneurs worldwide. The flip side is that the U.S. could be left behind if our regulators are overly aggressive. Rather than, once again, render early stage investing in the U.S. to the exclusive province of venture capitalists, regulators and the industry should work towards better disclosures and rules that guarantee investor rights.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Investors should be wary of easy money: </span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">As the old saying goes, if something seems too good to be true, it probably is… The siren song of the ICO market attracted both investors interested in making long-term, potential life-changing investments as well as those looking for a quick buck. There were two major differences, however, between the VCs, who had cornered the market on early stage investing, and the ICO phenomenon. First, and most important, the individual investors targeted by ICOs couldn’t perform due diligence or request the type of investor protections granted VC firms. (This, in part, explains why ICOs were so popular among founders for raising money). Those founders were able to get away with this, however, due to the second difference: many projects were able to promise immediate liquidity by virtue of crypto “exchanges” listing and trading the tokens. This added substantially to the allure of these assets and helped high pressure sales tactics succeed. I said earlier that this was reminiscent of the internet bubble, since ICO sales were quite similar to the tactics of “boiler room” OTC stock salespeople. Those assets also had instant liquidity and displayed prices on the pink sheets that often-showed meteoric price rises. The ability to demonstrate that early investors made fortunes was a major component of the appeal of these assets. Unfortunately, when the music stopped, most investors lost money.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The lesson here is that early stage investments (i.e., without actual products and revenue) should be treated the same, whether “securities” or not. Rather than outdated rules that fail to stop the problem, the companies who control such assets and those who sell them should disclose everything material to the sale, be held to strict guidelines of customer suitability and there should be strict enforcement of rules against fraud.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">When a lot of money is involved, fraud will follow: </span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">This is pretty obvious, considering human nature, but it is important to keep in mind. The only reason I identified this as a separate lesson is to remind us that we should not dismiss an entire technology due to the fact that it attracted fraudsters. Every time there is a technology that looks like it could be transformational, whether the internet, genetic biotechnology, energy breakthroughs or blockchain, it attracts a mix of legitimate firms and scam artists. It is a shame that this happens, and tarnishes the entire industry for a while, but it also seems to be inevitable.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">When fraud becomes rampant, regulators will react: </span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">As sure as day follows night, when people are defrauded, regulators will try to do something to prevent it from happening in the future. Sometimes the rules make sense, and sometimes they don’t, so the key for legitimate industries is to work with regulators rather than object & complain. While not a panacea, the best step is usually some form of industry cooperation and self-regulation. The good news is that seems to be what is happening with crypto.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Financial markets have evolved for important reasons, and crypto markets should embrace them: </span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">All of the negative stories occurred as most of the early adopters and technologists that drove crypto innovation had little knowledge of how financial markets operate AND have core beliefs which conflict with key established principles of investor protection, price discovery, and best execution.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Investor protection</span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> — Modern financial markets have evolved with rules that attempt to ensure that markets are fair and that investors are protected against unscrupulous attempts to take advantage of them. These range from customer suitability rules to mandatory financial disclosures, to market structure rules that guarantee fair access. In crypto, however, there are many issuers and market models that, on purpose, ignore these principles. Issuers and their advisors who pursue “non-dilutive capital” epitomize this, but the concept of caveat emptor goes further. There are exchanges that are </span><a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2018/09/18/ny-ag-cryptocurrency-exchanges-are-ripe-for-manipulation.html\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">willfully ignorant of manipulation taking place on their market</span></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">, and others whose </span><a href=\"https://cryptoslate.com/upbit-crypto-exchange-executives-indicted-for-market-manipulation/\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">employees have been accused of being complicit in such activ</span></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ities. Others ha</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ve made public statements that manipulation is not their concern. As an aside, the SEC has made it clear that rectifying this situation and establishing a culture of compliance is a necessary precondition for them approving a </span><a href=\"https://www.okex.me/academy/en\"><span class=\"15\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bitcoin</span></a><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> ETF. All of that said, institutions typically avoid markets they feel are rigged against them, and the only way to convince them markets are fair is a clear rulebook being followed.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><b><span class=\"16\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Price Discovery/Best Execution </span></b><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">— Modern financial markets are based on the premise that all participants know the price of assets and that such prices are determined fairly in a transparent manner. As a result, price discovery is a primary goal of markets, while the concept of best execution (meaning clients should have a realistic expectation of receiving the best price when they trade) is essential for investors to have confidence in markets. In order for price discovery to be maximized, however, there is a need for client orders to interact or, at a minimum, have information about prices on other markets. Yet, the crypto markets are fragmented on purpose. The dominant exchanges ignore prices available elsewhere while peer-to-peer markets are being built without consolidated pricing. Meanwhile popular crypto websites are often consistently wrong in the prices they report due to averaging together prices from jurisdictions that trade at a premium or prices based on different funding currencies. What is needed, therefore, are consolidated price feeds, such as CoinRoutes provides, becoming ubiquitous and authoritative.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"p\" style=\"margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;\r\nmargin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">In conclusion, the excesses of the crypto markets over the past two years should be a wake-up call to the industry and the regulators attempting to reform it. Understanding how financial markets operate and incorporating the types of technologies and rules which protect investors while improving market integrity is exactly what the crypto markets require. Considering the potential for digital assets to improve the banking system and capital markets allowing entrepreneurs worldwide to connect with capital, this should be a vital step forward.</span><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';font-size:10.5000pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;\"><o:p> </o:p></span></p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (110, 67, 'zh-CN', '啊啊啊', '<p>阿斯顿接口设计</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (111, 68, 'zh-CN', '比特币数字资产技术指标', '<p>无论是股票投资者还是投资者，技术分析在交易中都是非常重要的一环，对历史价格变动走势以及其他跟交易相关数据的研究，可以帮助我们找到交易时机以及预测价格变动方向。技术分析在股票、期货、商品交易、外汇以及其他资产类别中广泛应用。在数字货币时代，交易者在努力开发一些更符合这种极速增长的资产的分析工具，同时也将技术分析这种传统金融的方式带到了数字资产领域。</p><p>布林带 Bollinger Bands</p><p>布林带可以说是在交易中应用得最多的指标，以一位美国资管经理和技术分析专家约翰 布林(John Bollinger)命名。由一组描述以价格均线（通常是20-SMA）为基准的标准差正反两条线表示出布林带的范围。因为标准差是波动量的观测指标，当市场价格波动剧烈则布林带相对更宽，通常被认为是出场的信号，而在波动较小的时候布林带收缩，这可能是波动加剧的潜在信号，一般会作为入场信号。也有很多交易者认为当价格趋近于布林带的上线，是表示市场超买，相反的，当价格向下趋近布林带的下线，是表示市场超卖。</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (112, 69, 'zh-CN', '比特币期现套利策略报告', '<p>之前我们发布了一项关于研究现货杠杆费率与永续合约资金费率之间的关系从而寻找套利契机的报告，报告显示7日内的投资回报率为1.66%。然而这种操作最好是在OKEx这样既提供交割合约/永续合约 又提供现货交易的一站式服务交易所，这样可以免去提币矿工费用和链上转账时间。</p><p>这篇文章中，我们将介绍一种更传统的，期现套利，这种策略也可以在OKEx上使用。</p><p>什么是期现套利策略</p><p>货价格反映了市场上投资者对特定标的信心。每当市场波动，现货价格和期货价格就会大相径庭（基差），价格差异越明显越有利于套利。</p><p>在正常情况下，季度合约比当周合约和双周合约有更大的基差，因为离合约到期越久不确定因素就越多，因此我们在这篇文章中将以季度合约为例进行研究。</p><p>如果我们看上图，我们就可以知道基差的最高点是7月10号的581.7，然后在7月17号跌至-121.64，并且反弹至100-200的区间。</p><p>通过绘制基差随时间变化（每小时），我们可以知道这种合约的基差在7月份的大多数时间都在100-200之间波动。</p><p>实操</p><p>在现货市场上买入1000USDT的BTC，转入交割合约账户然后开空十张季度合约，其价值等同于1,000 USD，所有仓位都保持Delta中性（持有的头寸组合的Delta值为0，也就是BTC的价格变动不会影响最终的收益）。</p><p>如果你账户里只持有BTC，那你可以通过杠杆借USDT，然后重复上述流程。不过，由于这样需要收杠杆利息，那么最终你的收益则会低一些。</p><p>案例1：</p><p>以1,000 USDT为起始资本，在7月10日上午11点采用期现套利策略开仓，在7月17日0：00基差为负时平仓并计算收益：</p><p>案例2：</p><p>以0.1BTC作为初始资本，利用杠杆借币借得1000USDT并采用期现套利策略，在7月10日上午11:00 开仓，在7月17日0:00 基差为负时平仓并计算收益：</p><p>基差</p><p>如果基差一直保持上升不下降，这种投资组合可能会有暂时性的损失，但是离合约到期越近，基差会逐渐趋近于0。</p><p>波动</p><p>如果你的仓位比较重，在平仓的时候需要一定的时间仓位才能被市场消化，你的成本则会受到平仓过程中基差变动的影响。</p><p>USDT价格</p><p>USDT的美元价格让人提不起劲儿，而现货市场开仓就相当于卖掉USDT换美金。</p><p>强平风险</p><p>如果以USDT作为起始资金则没有强平风险，但是利用杠杆借币的交易者，可能会因为市场波动一次次追加保证金以避免爆仓。</p><p>优化</p><p>应该更细化地分析基差，采样时间间隔的粒度可以细化到“分”级别而不是“小时”级别。</p><p>使用OKEx上的交易大数据分析市场，以便更好地找到开仓和平仓的操作点从而获利，例如负基差的情况在7月出现了两次，我们可以考虑在负基差的时候开仓，当基差为正的时候平仓。</p><p>在交割之前，BTC的收益是不能转入现货账户的，为了避免BTC价格的波动风险，我们可以持有合约仓位或杠杆仓位来对冲掉风险。</p>', NULL);
INSERT INTO `article_translations` VALUES (113, 70, 'zh-CN', '比特币投资组合的风险对冲', '<p>受到主导的加密货币，自6月底达到13900美元的年度高位以来一直处于下行路径，比特币多头一直处于艰难境地。随着价格调整的继续，交易员们一直在寻找如何对冲他们的BTC多头头寸。由于蓬勃发展的加密衍生品市场，参与者现在可以利用日益流行的永续掉期和期货合约产品来更好地控制其风险敞口。</p><p>BTC短期看跌</p><p>尽管长期看涨形势仍然强劲，但在每日BTC/USDT交易对的K线图中可以看到持续的短期看跌情绪。6月下旬，BTC/USDT交易对在一年多以来，首次突破13900美元的价格水平，然而，该交易对未能在7月中旬继续突破该价格水平，因此形成了阻力位，即双顶模式之后将是下跌趋势。最近，BTC/USDT未能保持在双顶领口之上，该价位约为10400美元，更为重要的是，日线图的RSI指数仍然低于50并且MACD仍处于看跌区间。</p><p>衍生品和风险管理</p><p>鉴于BTC最近的价格调整，使用比特币衍生工具管理风险现在成为每个人都想重新审视的话题。如果是传统金融市场的投资者，应该对衍生品交易不会感到陌生。</p><p>在教科书中，衍生工具是一种金融证券，其价值由其相关资产决定。这是一项涉及两方或多方的合同，相关资产可以是股票、债券、商品、货币、利率或市场指数。</p><p>为何衍生品如此受欢迎？因为它可以用来对冲头寸，推测相关资产的定向变动，或者对持股进行杠杆化。在风险管理方面，它也是一种多功能的工具。作为风险分散策略的一部分，许多金融机构不断交易掉期和远期等衍生品。</p><p>数字货币领域的衍生品</p><p>与传统的衍生品市场相比，数字货币的合约市场是相对较新且较小的，但这并不表示数字货币市场并非是无利可图的。与股票期货或利率掉期相似，BTC衍生品可以避免数字货币市场的波动以及价格变化，并且可以作为抵消潜在损失的对冲工具。</p><p>最重要的是，交易者可以利用合约来推测具有杠杆作用的数字货币的价格，从而最大化潜在的利润。数字货币世界中有三种主要的合约产品为（1）永续合约；（2）期货合约；（3）期权合约。</p><p>套期保值</p><p>尽管BTC的下行风险越来越大，最终可能为BTC多头创造买入机会，但BTC负面情绪已经增强，而且对于风险管理，建议投资者审查其套期保值和套利策略。套期保值涉及在相反方向使用多个并发投注，以试图限制严重的投资损失风险。首先，让我们回顾一下对冲策略之间的差异。</p><p>让我们以交割合约作为对冲的一个例子。</p><p>还有一些其他因素会影响整体对冲策略，例如合约交割日，做多或做空的决定以及合约数量。</p><p>保护多头头寸</p><p>永续合约是投资者可以利用的另一种结构性工具，我们假设现货市场的价格为9500美元，而BTC永续合约交易价格为9600美元。投资者可以在现货市场以9500美元的价格，并在同一时间在永续合约市场中开出价值相同（9500美元）的空头头寸。</p><p>1. 当BTC的价格上涨时，投资者可以从现货市场中获利。</p><p>2. 当BTC的价格下跌时，投资者可以平仓永续合约的空头头寸并从中获利，弥补现货市场的损失。</p><p>但是，如果长期持有合约是其策略的一部分，交易者还应考虑融资和结算因素。</p><p>套利机会</p><p>套利是为了从非均衡市场中获利，在多个市场之间交易同一商品价差的做法，它涉及在很短的时间内购买和出售商品。我们假设现货市场比特币交易价格为9500美元，而BTC永续合约价格为9600美元。投资者以9500美元的价格在现货市场购买比特币，并在同一时间在永续合约中开出价值相同（9600美元）的空头头寸。</p><p>1. 如果两者之间的利差缩小，投资者可以获利。</p><p>2. 如果差价扩大，交易的未实现损益变为负值。在这种情况下，投资者可以等待到期结算。合约的标记价格通常根据现货价格计算，因此标记价格非常接近现货价格，利润约为9600-9500美元 = 100美元</p><p>3. 当现货价格高于合约价格时，总利润超过100美元。</p><p>结论</p><p>套期保值不是追求无风险交易。相反，它是在交易时减少已知风险的尝试。这是传统金融市场和业务管理中的一项重要策略，数字货币交易者可以采用在股票、外汇和商品交易中广泛使用的做法。与任何其他风险/回报交易非常相似，套期保值会导致相关方的回报率降低，但它可以提供重要的下行风险保护。</p><p><br></p>', NULL);
